(16,	3,	2,	1,	'2012-01-20',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Provided revised bullets on 1/17/12 to the email provided by Kaveh in regards to WO 600\'s support of the New Media Strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Met  with Al\'Tariq on 1/17/12 to discuss WO 600\'s/Kaveh\'s email.&nbsp; He thought  the revised bullets were a good idea and has a meeting scheduled with  Kaveh on 1/17/12.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Al\'Tariq on 1/18/12 to discuss New Media Strategy status and meeting with Ronnie.&nbsp; We discussed the Next Steps and Concerns from WO 600.&nbsp; Updated presentation to include Ronnies Next Steps and the Interdiciplinary Teams Next Steps along with a slide noting major concerns for meeting with Ronnie on 1/18/12.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Ronnie and Al\'Tariq on 1/18/12 to discuss presentation and meeting with the Exective Team.&nbsp; Ronnie approved the presentaiton and requested that the Next Steps slide be combined.&nbsp; She also requested that we meet with the executives individually prior to a meeting with the entire team.&nbsp; This includes a meetin with NPS and Neil Kornze.</p>\r\n<p>Updated presentation for the Executive Team on 1/19/12 to include combined Next Steps and deleted the Concerns slide.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed NPS\'s&nbsp; most recent updates the their Social Media Policy on 1/19/12 and sent an email to Ms. Levine and Al\'Tariq noting concerns that their process does not align with the process that she has discussed. The email asked if she was still interested in the meeting under these circumstances.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discussed the postponed ITIB with Rich D. on 1/17/12. He stated that there would probaly be a meeting towards the end on February.</p>\r\n<p>Provided Beth with information on 1/1712 regarding the ITIB and provided feedback to her concerns regarding the scope of the Investment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred on 1/17/12 to discuss Acquisition Strategy documenta