7-2012. Discussed how they need to better define the communication problem they are looking to fix before getting too far down the process, discussed which groups of people are they trying to improve communications with. &nbsp; Discussed how they currently communicate with these groups and how do they envision to communicate with these groups in the future. &nbsp;We are going to further discuss this issue on next week when we have more time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">None at this time.</span></p>',	'<p><span style=\"background-color: #fafafa;\">None at this time.</span></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-01-23 15:19:02',	6,	'2012-01-25 03:32:15'),
(18,	3,	2,	1,	'2012-01-27',	'<p><strong>New Media</strong></p>\r\n<p>Requested Marti set up the individual meetings with Ms. Levine and each of the memebrs if Core Team of Executives on 1/23/12.&nbsp; Sent followup requests on 1/24/12 and 1/26/12.&nbsp; Sent requests to Al\'Tariq on 1/26/12 and he followed up with the request on 1/27/12.</p>\r\n<p>Discussed Oregons efforts with Ms. Levine on 1/24/12.&nbsp; Updated New Media Presentation to include Ms. Levines requests and sent it to Ms. Levine on 1/24/12.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed and updated New Media Strategy so that the Next Steps aligned with the presentation on 1/25/12.</p>\r\n<p>Provided feedback to Alexandra Ritchie\'s email request for the status of the New Media Strategy on 1/25/12 per Al\'Tariq\'s request.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Geospatial Publication Investment</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth on 1/24/12 to discuss the status of the Investment.&nbsp; There has not been much progress due to her move.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth on 1/26/12 to discuss IM\'s relating to web policies and geospatial data publication.&nbsp; She wanted to ensure that they were within policy boundaries.&nbsp; Worked with Brian Anthony to get a list of applicable IM\'s.&nbsp; Fred also provided me with a link to IM\'s online.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Beth and GPI team on 1/26/12 to discuss requirements and exisitng systems.&nbsp; To the best of our knowledge, an inventory of existing viewers and mapping services does not exist.&nbsp; We discussed possibilities for collecting the data for the inventory.&nbsp; I provided an email request to Patrick and Al\'tariq to see if we had any type of exisitng information.&nbsp; Patrick responed on 1/27/12 with an additional point of contact.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SLM</strong></p>\r\n<p>Met with Fred and Al\'Tariq on 1/24/12 to discuss CPIC\'s comments in regards to the SLM.&nbsp; Several comments had little applicability. The overall issue seems to be that the process is not owned by their division.&nbsp; Fred is provi