t: -0.75in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 2.75in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level5 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">1.3.3.3.5</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Service Catalogue and Service Level Agreements</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.75in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 2.75in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level5 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">1.3.3.3.6</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Data Quality and Data Integrity</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.5in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 1.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level3 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">1.3.4</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">TBD</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -0.5in; margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1.5in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level3 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">1.3.5</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">TBD</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Configuration Management Plan</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">I conducted a second review of the draft Configuration Management Plan and prepared a spreadsheet of comments and revisions to be given to Naomi.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; One of my&nbsp;comments is</span>&nbsp;that the CM plan be championed by WO-570 so it is within the context of the overall IT Service Operations Plan and the Integrated Lifecycle Framework.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On Tuesday, April 3rd Mohammad and I held an 11am initial meeting to discuss PMO activities and the manner in which projects have been led within BLM Washington Offices (WO\'s), the Network Operation Center, eleven states, and other national centers.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">On Tuesday, April 3rd, Christine and I held an afternoon meeting to discuss the status of data standardization.<a></a></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; Prior to the meeting, I was given a&nbsp;preliminiary draft&nbsp;document of BLM\'s enterprise architecture tool planning.&nbsp;&nbsp; This document was not discussed in the meeting.&nbsp; The meeting largely addressed various miscellaneous topics associated with abandoned IBM System Architect data files, &nbsp;the Deparment of Interior and BLM Enterprise Repositories, DEAR and BEAR respectively.</span></p>\r\n</span></span>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">On Tuesday,&nbsp;April 3<sup>rd</sup>, Al&rsquo;Tariq spoke with Mohammad and I at 4:30pm about the following three activities:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Enterprise Architecture, PMO, and IT Services. Al&rsquo;Tariq expressed that the outline for EA framework was previously done or near completion.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>He directed that Mohammad continue to lead EA activity. I will offer and provide support in any and all areas requested.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">There are no project issues or problems.</span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">na</span></span></span></span></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-04-08 22:27:16',	4,	'2012-04-10 20:55:45'),
(35,	12,	2,	1,	'2012-04-13',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Enterprise Architecture</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">To kickoff the EA project within WO-570, I was asked by Mohammad to share with him information about my experience with the Department of Defense Architecture Framework or DoDAF.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>To comply with this request I have reviewed several documents including old and current DoDAF training materials and am reading through the Federal Chief Information Officer Council Guide to Federal Enterprise Architecture.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>The Practical Guide to FEA published by the CIO Council is a companion document to the FEA Consolidated Reference Model which outlines the reference models that BLM programs and applications have been mapped to in legacy documentation.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Much of the current documentation related to BLM&rsquo;s EA requires extensive updates, and consequently a review of recommended practices for EA is also essential.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>All of the aforementioned background is necessary to develop and execute a value-added EA plan that defines and meets the needs and expectations of BLM.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>One of the main goals behind EA is to document &ldquo;As-Is&rdquo; or current state, and facilitate appropriate data driven decisions about IT investments that impact the BLM \"future state\".</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Another aspect of the EA project involves updating legacy spreadsheet data to enhance BLM&rsquo;s view of its software assets for all projects, and across all server systems for the field offices, each district, state and various centers including the NOC.&nbsp;&nbsp; I&nbsp;will continue to update the CTO Unified Spreadsheet and incorporate requests that are made by&nbsp;Patrick Stingley.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">GIS Render Farm</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Research of render farm organizations and&nbsp;operations&nbsp;in order to&nbsp;define&nbsp;the High Performance or optimized GIS Mission Needs Statement and technical requirements specification.</span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Enterprise Architecture</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">I prepared for the initial EA discussion and updated a previous draft of the following Enterprise Architecture project strawman to present to Mohammad and Patrick for their consideration. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.75in; mso-add-space: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">1.1</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt