(42,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-04-27',	'<p>Was advised by Mr. Samuels that my recent activities incorporating a document furnished by CTO into the ILM&nbsp;were not a welcome change, and that I had failed to follow through on his directive.&nbsp; The document was a detailed&nbsp;schedule breakdown of the overall life cycle&nbsp;process and implied certain refinements/alterations to the baseline document.</p>\r\n<p>After a&nbsp;short period of&nbsp;confusion, I had a good discussion and clarification with Mr. Samuels, and he has assigned Ms. Bowers to work closely with me in the upcoming time.&nbsp;&nbsp; We have held a couple meetings and several email back-and-forths in preparing to relaunch next week.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ms. Bowers has asked me to re-start the editing process I had begun several weeks ago, but&nbsp;to not make changes to the document until they were reviewed/approved, using the \"Track Changes\" function in Word.&nbsp; In addition, she has noted that the ITIB will require a summary presentation for the 3-day&nbsp;June 5 meeting where the ILM will be presented. I will begin working on that presentation next week.</p>',	'<p>Restarted editing, conceptualizing&nbsp;effort,&nbsp;with clearer direction.</p>',	'<p>Mr. Samuels &amp; Mr. Lewis; Ms. Bowers; Staff Meeting.</p>\r\n<p>Attended Data Call telecon with Ms. Hawkinson on Monday to become involved in the effort to harness the wide variety of data calls putting onus on the field offices and especially the NOC.</p>',	'<p>Hopefully, no further issues after this week.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-04-27 16:43:43',	13,	'2012-05-08 15:16:42'),
(43,	12,	2,	1,	'2012-04-27',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Enterprise Architecture</span> -<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>A critical component of the EA is the PMO, and the establishment of a performance measurement system.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Therefore, I reviewed the ANSI/EIA 748 standards for earned value management (EVM) and related maturity models that might be considered by WO-570 in its goals to establish a PMO with performance measurement expectations.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Performance measurement will allow BLM to simultaneously monitor cost and schedule performance on projects and establish a standard method of assessment throughout BLM consistent with Enterprise Architecture initiatives.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>It is believed that a gradual and steady performance measurement approach can be achieved without heavy investment in EVM software tools (e.g. Deltek Winsight, OpenPlan, Primavera).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>However, BLM should consider these or similar tools over time.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I have begun to benchmark EVM tools to support decision makers with BLM who will make decisions about performance measurement.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>In accordance with the EVM maturity model, WO-570 can optimize project performance over five successive stages and address the following;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Need recognition for a performance measurement system within all of BLM</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Alignment of current performance measurement activities with key process areas for EVM maturation and the ANSI/EIA 748.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Such alignment will have the effect of placing appropriate amount of focus on organizational, planning, accounting, analysis, and revision process areas</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">-</span><span style=\"line-height: normal; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Goals of the EA such as the Integrated Lifecycle Management System and Project Management </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">The enterprise architecture task list provided to Mohammad should include EVM.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Highly Optimized GIS Mission Needs Statement</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Per an earlier discussion with Patrick, I have the task of researching methods to optimize a render farm for BLM GIS applications. In addition to contacting companies that provide render farm services, I am discussing and learning about the process of rendering an image and the elimination of bottlenecks based on a pipelined architecture that has application, geometry and rasterizer conceptual stages.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Lessons gained will help create an architecture that will be shared with Patrick who will present technical suggestions within the BLM organization.</span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Enterprise Architecture</span> - I prepared a template which can be used to compare and contrast major industry performance measurement system tools.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>I have reviewed several documents on the EVM Maturity Model, and complete 30% of a performance measurement handbook on EVM.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>This handbook also makes reference to project reprogramming and rebaselining requirements for IT projects.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">PMO</span> &ndash; Draft documents of the Project Management Plan were prepared for review with Mohammad who indicated that his intent to share ideas with me about the PMO structure and policy related matters.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"line-height: 115%; color: black; font-size: 10pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Specifically, I worked on a Quality Management Plan, and supported revision of the Configuration </span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Management Handbook draft based on email request from Naomi.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">na</span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">na</span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">na</span></span></span></span></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-04-30 00:48:31',	NULL,	'2012-05-04 12:01:32'),
(44,	9,	2,	1,	'2012-01-06',	'<p>testing</p>',	'<p>testing</p>',	'<p>testing</p>',	'<p>testing</p>',	'<p>testing</p>',	2,	8,	'2012-05-01 05:36:18',	NULL,	'2012-05-01 06:13:51'),
(45,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-05-04',	'<p>Assigned by Ms. Bowers to create the June 5 ITIB Integrated Lifecycle Management&nbsp;presentation.&nbsp; She supplied some content that I have turned into presentation form, working on graphics and editing, first reviewable draft neaxt week.</p>\r\n<p>Was directed to restart the ILM edit&nbsp;from a clean original document.&nbsp; Re-edited the first section and turned in for review, still pending.</p>\r\n<p>Spent time researching Information Assurance and other lifecycle frameworks, e.g. COBIT.&nbsp; COBIT makes an interesting distinction between Governance and Management of IT activities.&nbsp; My understanding from Mr. Samuels is that all of 500&nbsp;is involved in governance.&nbsp; I presume that leaves the NOC in the management role.</p>',	'<p>First draft of June presentation.</p>\r\n<p>I believe what we are building is an Integrated Lifecycle <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Governance</span> methodology (ILG).&nbsp; This moniker seems to fit better with the role of 570 and all of WO500.</p>\r\n<p>Created a definition of ILM (works even better for ILG), which I believe to be in line with Mr. Samuels directive that the SLM/ILM Handbook is a Governance document:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><strong><em><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">A methodology for applying IT Governance Processes, including Investment Management (CPIC), Strategic Alignment (EA)&nbsp;and Information Security(IA), to achieve successful Information Technology projects that support BLM strategic goals and meet user needs.</span></em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>Called the two people Mr. Samuels directed me to contact; have not heard back from either.&nbsp; Mr. Samuels is aware of the first, only called the second once (Thursday), will attempt again on Mon.</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-05-04 16:54:41',	NULL,	'2012-05-08 21:13:46'),
(46,	12,	2,	1,	'2012-05-04',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Enterprise Architecture &ndash; I followed up on&nbsp;performance measurement&nbsp;activities&nbsp;from the previosus week and reviewed the functions of the BLM Capital Planning and Investment Control (CPIC) Group as they are identified in the BLM CPIC Handbook.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The purpose was to determine what performance measurement activities are specifically addressed by CPIC and how pr if BLM makes use of earned value management as a method of performance measurement.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I also reviewed program management requirements stated in Office of Management and Budget (OMB) Circulars 11 and 300 and sought specific examples of BLM reports based on these two government requirements.&nbsp; </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: #000000; font-size: small;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Highly Optimized GIS Mission Needs Statement</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">There is no significant change in status from the prior week other than ongoing research of methods to optimize a render farm for BLM GIS applications. Prior efforts have included establishing contact companies that provide render farm services, review of render farm architectures.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Also, cloud-based rendering concepts are one of the items that I am continuing to explore as an option to a typical non cloud-based render farm architecture.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Enterprise Architecture - I updated a template which can be used to compare and contrast major industry performance measurement system tools, and have continued to improve a performance measurement handbook based on EVM.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The handbook makes reference to the EVM maturity model in addition to reprogramming and rebaselining requirements for IT projects.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">PMO - Discovered useful templates for WO-570 personnel to review.</span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">NA</span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">NA</span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">NA</span></span></span></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-05-07 05:35:39',	NULL,	'2012-05-08 15:33:06'),
(47,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-05-11',	'<p>Was informed on Monday that we would not do a presentation of the ILM at the June ITIB, we should just get the document out.&nbsp; Did a flash edit on a clean February version, capturing some of what I had done previously.&nbsp; Updated the graphics to reflect new concepts from before my arrival and the name change.&nbsp; Created a greatly expanded glossary to cover virtually all terms used in the document growing from 5 pages to 15.</p>',	'<p>The ILM Technical Manual will be ready for&nbsp;distribution to BLM&nbsp;reviewers&nbsp;Monday, 5/14, assuming Ms. Bowers signs off on the changes.</p>',	'<p>Several brief meetings with Ms. Bowers to discuss various changes to the ILM document and next steps for moving forward.&nbsp; She will send the document out to various team members for review and comment.</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>Believe Ms. Bowers will seek approval for distribution of ILM document.</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-05-11 16:42:03',	13,	'2012-05-18 07:47:45'),
(48,	14,	8,	1,	'2012-05-11',	'<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin: auto auto auto 114pt; mso-add-space: auto;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; mso-bidi-font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Project:<span style=\"mso-tab-count: 1;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>MDT </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Finalized SOW</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"color: black; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Reviewed Tribalco IDIQ</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 3;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">MDT Devices</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 3;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span></span></strong><span style=\"color: black; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Developed and submitted&nbsp;change management request to allow Panasonic TB19 and TB31</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 3;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">ADORE System</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 3;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"><span style=\"color: black; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Completed change management request to allow the usage of the Adore System to remedy the following requirement:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-style: italic; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Both DOI and BLM policy require the FTEP be successfully completed, and BLM policy requires that the specific BAPs and SEGs be adhered to.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Ensuring consistency and proper administration of the program is imperative to ensure that disciplinary actions are upheld.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The current system does not lend itself well to that proper documentation.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 3;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">DOI IMARS System</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 3;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"><span style=\"color: black; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Research existing CAD system that are current compatible with the IMARS system.&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"><span style=\"color: black; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">EIS and Motorola Solutions are the only two vendors that have proven to be successfully integrated with IMARS and DOI blessed.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Both those vendors are on the Tribalco IDIQ.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 3;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 3;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"></span></span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; mso-bidi-font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Project:<span style=\"mso-tab-count: 1;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>AFMSS </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Business case documents preparation and reviews</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"></span></span></strong><span style=\"color: black; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Development of the alternatives analysis and cost analysis documentation<strong></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"><span style=\"color: black; mso-fareast-font-family: Wingdings; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; mso-bidi-font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Project:<span style=\"mso-tab-count: 1;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>NFLSS</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"color: black;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\">&