(50,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-05-18',	'<p>Delivered final version of the ILM to Ms. Bowers Monday noon. Her intent was to seek approval to distribute for comment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Received new assignment to review Acquisition, Change, Quality, Requirements Management Templates and search for BLM \"Standards\" or DOI Standards to insert into the documents, emphasis on Acquisition and Quality.&nbsp; Directed to contact Kim Ashby regarding acquisition--she was out Thurs/Fri.&nbsp;&nbsp; Also asked to remove duplicative wording from Scope and Charter Templates.&nbsp; Latter effort is easy, but&nbsp;I searched all over the BLM websites and Sharepoiint sites with little success; I found numerous \"data quality&nbsp;\" standards, but nothing useful for IT systems quality.&nbsp; Found some potentially useful info on the National Test Center Site (instructions for ordering software/hardware testing), but no standards.&nbsp; Agreed with Ms. Bowers that we\'d reexamine next week.</p>\r\n<p>New assignment Friday to review all 570 projects with project managers to determine current status, where they are in the ILM schema (if they are being operated that way).&nbsp; Ms. Bowers will send out a notice that I am to contact all PMs for status report.&nbsp; Once that is complete, task will be to find out status on all of the other projects being run outside 570.</p>',	'<p>Concluded work on the Integrated Lifecycle Management Technical Manual.</p>',	'<p>Short meetings with Ms. Bowers to discuss steps for accomplishing the new assignments, obtaining her suggestions on how to proceed (e.g., see Kim Ashby for acquisition matters).</p>',	'<p>None (except I can\'t find any Standards)</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-05-18 15:54:15',	NULL,	'2012-05-29 14:59:00'),
(51,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-05-25',	'<p>Received new assignment last Friday: Review all open projects in&nbsp;WO 570,&nbsp;based on matrix compiled by Ken Greenberger, with each Lead/PM.&nbsp; Determine which are \"projects\" that should fall within the purview of the ILM and determine current status/phase. Also determine status on non-project staff work (e.g., ILM, Mobile Device Management Policy, etc).&nbsp; Began conducting interviews with each lead person.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When interviews are complete will deliver a revised spreadsheet showing updated status, separating staff work from project work.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Received a rejection from Directives&nbsp;Branch of IRM Governance&nbsp;of ILM draft due to format issues (indentation <em>before</em> bullets, not after; too many different fonts; et. al).&nbsp; Did a fast revision to comply with their dictates on Monday for (re)-distribution Tuesday.</p>',	'<p>Conducted half of the status update interviews.</p>\r\n<p>Finalized ILM review draft (again).</p>\r\n<p>Delivered revised Scope Statement and Project Charter templates to Ms. Bowers (task was to eliminate redundancy--remove scope issues from Charter).&nbsp; Did some minor editing/tweaking.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed draft Data Management Handbook (Christine Hawkinson\'s activity)</p>\r\n<p>It may be a negative accomplishment, but I&nbsp;learned through project review meeting with Christine&nbsp;that there is (I think)&nbsp;an insignificant hole in the ILM; her data management/data quality handbook&nbsp;activities likely dovetail with the ILM, since, after all, Information Technology is&nbsp;really about&nbsp;data. There are a couple of project deliverables that would naturally result in an IT project, e.g., a \"Data Management Plan\" which&nbsp;are not addressed&nbsp;in the current version of the ILM.&nbsp; Will probably need to meet to discuss next steps.</p>',	'<p>Held project review sessions with Brian Anthony, Christine Hawkinson, Naomi Bowers, Mohammad Haniffa, Patrick S