(53,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-06-01',	'<p>Finalized Project review document, interviewing remaining staff members (with exception of Ms. Slocum, who is on maternity leave).&nbsp; Turned in to Ms. Bowers, I assume it goes to Mr. Samuels now.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unclear&nbsp;whether this will become&nbsp;a recurring activity or a one-off.</p>\r\n<p>Continued working on ILM templates; obtained IT Acquisition Services (WO550)&nbsp;documents that describe the process of creating an acquisition strategy and managment&nbsp;plan&nbsp;from their vantage, incorporated into the ILM Acquisition Plan Template draft.</p>\r\n<p>Mr. Samuels advised I will be receiving additional taskings next week: Governance document review for Mr. Smith; assistance in drawing specifications for an EA tool (and other tools) working with Mr. Haniffa, Ms. Hawkinson, Mr. Stingley.</p>\r\n<p>ILM Handbook is under outside&nbsp;review.</p>',	'<p>Finished first draft of Project Review Document.</p>\r\n<p>Delivered draft of Acquisition Strategy &amp; Management plan</p>',	'<p>Met with 570 staff members to determine the status of their projects:&nbsp; Mr. Lewis, Mr. Greenberger, Mr. Smith, Mr. Hanniffa.</p>\r\n<p>With Ms. Bowers, met with Directives (WO560) personnel to resolve issues of \"Plain Language\" in the ILM Handbook.&nbsp; (Document was twice&nbsp;criticized as being too technically complex).&nbsp; In the opinion of the plain language SME in Directives, (who only received the document an hour earlier)&nbsp;document was appropriate as written for the expected audience.&nbsp; Discussed various formatting/spacing issues and will make corrections next week.</p>\r\n<p>Mike Smith advised he would be sending the SharePoint&nbsp;governance document to me next week&nbsp;and gave me a brief background on work to date.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-06-01 16:16:48',	13,	'2012-06-06 08:41:32'),
