(57,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-06-15',	'<p><span>Bulk of the week spent in activities surrounding Data Center Consolidation efforts.&nbsp; DOI guidance for end of quarter reporting required delivery of major spreadsheet report on 6/15.&nbsp; Considerable ongoing confusion around the fact that we have several more sites closed than are being reported.&nbsp; Strategic decision was made last year to keep some sites in our back pocket,&nbsp;keep to the overall schedule on track...substituting closed properties for those where we encounter problems.&nbsp; Several significant changes to the report format required detailed review of the entire (57-Site)&nbsp;document, although only 5 sites closed this quarter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Supported Mr. Stingley on drafting the DCCI transmittal letter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Next week will involve review of closure documents, which must be finalized for transmittal to DOI along with finalized spreadsheet report by 6/30/12.&nbsp; (Anticipating there will be questions on spreadsheet from DOI).</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Friday was deadline for comment submissions on ILM, so that work will resume next week.</span></p>',	'<p><span>&nbsp;Delivered completed, accurate DCCI report to DOI.</span></p>',	'<p><span>Two telecoms with Mr. Stingley, Mr. Ravenscroft (NOC Director), Mr. Torres (PM) to review the Data Center Consolidation Initiative (DCCI) spreadsheet report.&nbsp; First meeting was somewhat dicey with unhappy principals, questionable data;&nbsp;second, after significant input to&nbsp;Mr. Torres went&nbsp;very smoothly.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Met with Mr. Samuels and Mr. Stingley to review transmittal letter for DCCI submission to DOI.&nbsp;</span></p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-06-19 10:05:06',	4,	'2012-06-22 06:07:06'),
(58,	14,	8,	1,	'2012-06-15',	'<p>AFMSS - Prepared for the June 15 ITIB presentation. &nbsp;Worked on proposals with the NOC and WO-300. &nbsp;ONLY provided supporting industry documentation and projections related to costing.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Finalized acquisition strategy with government representatives. &nbsp;Provided the government with documentation only; did not engage in ANY conversations or decision making processes related to costing and contracting.</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC - Prepared for the June 15 ITIB presentation.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS - Completed AFMSS ITIB presentation. &nbsp;Met with government representatives to finalize proposals. &nbsp;Completed cost estimates for ITIB presentation. &nbsp;Presented (as a member of the government project team) the AFMSS and AFMSS APD presentation to BLM ITIB. &nbsp;Received project approval to proceed from ITIB.</p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC - Completed Mobility ITIB presentation. &nbsp;Met with government representatives to finalize proposals. &nbsp;Presented (as a member of the government project team) the Tablet PC &amp; Smartphone presentation to BLM ITIB. &nbsp;Received project approval to proceed from ITIB.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Successfully provided acquisition options to WO-120 DAD.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS - Jun 12 Meeting with WO-300 Project Team. &nbsp;Jun 13 Meeting with WO-300 and NOC to finalize presentation, &nbsp;Jun 15 &nbsp;Presented project projections presentation to ITIB.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Jun 11 Presented acquisition options to WO-120 Law Enforcement DAD.</p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC - Jun 15 Presented project projections presentations to ITIB.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p>AFMSS - None</p>\r\n<p>MDT - None</p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC - None.</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p>AFMSS - None</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Determine acquisition vehicle.</p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC - None.</p>\r\n</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-06-19 11:25:56',	4,	'2012-06-22 06:11:29'),
(59,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-06-22',	'<p>Spent much of the week finalizing site closure document details with NOC PM and Oregon data mgr.&nbsp;&nbsp;Made a number of detailed corrections to avoid incorrect reporting&nbsp;on staus of \"data centers\" that are now \"closed\" but have the same or greater numbers of servers to provide basic services to local staff (file/print servers, DNS servers, etc.)</p>\r\n<p>Also spent considerable time chasing resolution of a late-arriving piece of information that should have been included in previous week\'s data call submission.&nbsp; US Fish &amp; Wildlife Svc. has servers at BLM Nat\'nl Fire Center that have been reporposed, closing their reporting of the site as a data center, and according to DOI project personnel, are to be reported as if they are BLM equipment.&nbsp; Meeting early next week to discuss data call submission, so need to resolve reporting early Monday.</p>\r\n<p>Received&nbsp;three review submissions on draft ILM document, from CPIC, WO 200, Data Management (570).&nbsp; After review with Ms. Bowers, began editing comments into document.&nbsp; Meeting Monday PM with Mr. Samuels to review current status.</p>',	'<p>Completed Review and editing&nbsp;of closing documents for 5 Oregon sites.&nbsp; PM will present them to data manager for signature next week, WO 570 will deliver to DOI by Friday next week.</p>',	'<p>Numerous phone conferences ICW Data Center Closings.</p>\r\n<p>Bi-weekly staff meeting.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-06-25 09:19:56',	13,	'2012-06-29 22:45:54'),
(60,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-06-29',	'<p><!--StartFragment--></p>\r\n<p>Significant effort to apply accurate costs, repair formulas on closing documents for FDCCI project compliance.&nbsp; Planned forecast closure of five sites this quarter, and met successfully, on time. &nbsp;Wrote cover letter for delivery to DOI CIO signed by Mr. Samuels (acting ADIR), delivered documents to Mr. Stingley who forwarded to DOI PM via email.</p>\r\n<p>In prep for meeting with Mr. Samuels, Ms. Bowers, finalized a new version of the ILM, adding comments from WO 550, WO-300,&nbsp;Data Management in 570, and some from work with Ms. Bowers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!--EndFragment-->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Completed closing documents for five Oregon sites, adding, for the first time, additional telco and data center closure\'s labor costs.&nbsp; Late additions approved by WO 570 Director and NOC Director and State Data Advisor.&nbsp; Documents delivered to DOI.</p>',	'<p><!--StartFragment--></p>\r\n<p><!--StartFragment-->\r\n<p>Via Telecon, reviewed Data Call Submission with DOI PM and DPM, BLM CTO, PM tightening certain aspects to DOI liking.&nbsp; Finalized, made satisfactory to all with only minor revisions.</p>\r\n<!--EndFragment--></p>\r\n<p>Met with Mr. Samuels, MS Bowers to review status of ILM.&nbsp; Received guidance on Data Management comments, positioning of overall document within 500 (NOT 570), introduction of Program Management and PMO concepts into ILM, need for discussion of change and configuration management within ILM.&nbsp; Intent is to introduce program governance, not taking over functions of others, but positioning to ensure governance principles are enacted and planning precepts are followed, ensuring business requirements are obtained and addressed.</p>\r\n<!--EndFragment-->\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-07-01 16:38:12',	4,	'2012-07-06 11:39:39'),
(61,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-07-06',	'<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt;\">Produced a clean template for Data Center Closure Documents, making certain all formulas were in place and correct. In reviewing the documents submitted to DOI for FDCCI on 6/29, I discovered a small oversight in one tab&hellip;required a manual insertion of the data center name on one sheet, and we missed doing so on all of them.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>On advice of Mr. Stingley, revised and sent in a new FINAL version to the DOI Project Manager (and other involved parties).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>PM accepted and booked a review meeting for Monday 7/9.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">In an effort to get ahead of the curve on Data Center Closures, began drafting closure documents for the next six sites.&nbsp; Able to fill in most of the blanks, will finish my part next week. Will need field support in assigning serial numbers and a few other minor details, but should be a much easier process than the last couple of times.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I hope.</span></p>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt;\">Began reviewing the FDCCI planning documents from last year; will need to be replanned this August for 9/1 submission to DOI, appears that Mr. Stingley&rsquo;s expectation is that I will be redoing the plan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black; font-size: 7.5pt;\">Completed an edit of the ILM &amp; delivered to MS Bowers. Incorporated comments from WO 300, WO 550, Data Management in WO 570, and the results of the previous week\'s meeting w/ Mr. Samuels, Ms. Bowers. Document is approaching readiness, but Identified several areas that require some direction/decision making. Requested a meeting to review these open areas in the transmittal memo.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Finalized DCC closing sheets.</p>\r\n<p>Drafted next data center closure documents for 4QFY\'12.</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-07-03 15:11:45',	13,	'2012-07-12 22:07:20'),
