(71,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-07-27',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Began doing research for creating Enterprise Architecture templates for each application. Per Mr. Stingley, attempting to create a document that summarizes each system, populated by current data from CPIC (and other sources).<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Made a couple of initial attempts, was able to create a click-link that opens a SharePoint document bearing useful information, as<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>but the final result may require assistance from a programmer; Mr. Stingley&rsquo;s desire is to automatically populate our document with data from other sources.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">What Mr. Stingley actually wants is an ArcGIS Map for EA; click on an office, pull up all of the relevant information about that location in terms of the hardware and software configurations in place.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>To this end, I spent some time last week obtaining ESRI access for both local and national systems and in attempting to learn something of the software.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Received new assignment ICW DCCI&mdash;summary document displaying YE #data centers of two types (over/under 500sf) over the period 2011-2015.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Requires annual rack count, server count, cost savings by year.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>In process of working the document discovered several discrepancies in the data call reports to DOI for 2011, 2012, working to reconcile.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">ICW with the above, PM and I reconciled a strategy for the California State Office closing.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Office has actually moved all of its servers to BOR location, I generated closing documents for the CA IT personnel, we will report the center closed as of end of FY 4Q, in advance of original plan.</span></span></span></p>',	'<p>Generated new California State Office Closing Document</p>',	'<p>Attended weekly FDCCI telecon.&nbsp; Nothing controversial.</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-07-30 13:46:28',	NULL,	'2012-08-01 10:52:42'),
(72,	14,	8,	1,	'2012-07-27',	'<p>MDT:Began documentation for presentation to the ENDCAB for the ADORE application to be accessed by LEO use&nbsp;BLM wide.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: Began research on remote desktop solution to&nbsp;allow the LEO&rsquo;s to remotely access and control their desktop PCs from the iPad.&nbsp;&nbsp; This would allow users to have full functionality of their Bureau computers remotely.&nbsp; They would be able to access IMARS in addition to RadCom which is their dispatch software.&nbsp; Everything that is run on the PC such as ArcGIS could be run remotely through the iPad with such software.&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>MDT: Completed and submitted EAD documentation to procurement.</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: Completed and submitted NIFC request for pilot participation for android device testing.</p>\r\n<p>Submitted tablet pc acquisition report to the DOI.</p>',	'<p>MDT: Bi-weekly Law Enforcement MDT project team meeting.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS: Need clearly defined roles and responsibilities for the entire project.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS APD: Need clearly defined roles and responsibilities for the entire project.</p>\r\n<p>MDT: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Radio - Need assistance determining strategic goals priorities.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS: Need clearly defined roles and responsibilities for the entire project.</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS APD: Need clearly defined roles and responsibilities for the entire project.</p>\r\n<p>MDT: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tablet PC: None</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Radio - Need assistance determining strategic goals priorities.</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-07-31 15:25:56',	4,	'2012-08-01 10:54:54'),
(73,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-08-03',	'<p>Worked with Mr. Stingley to identify&nbsp; a way to set up SharePoint with a template document that when certain lines are clicked on, information is pulled from another document and displayed in Sharepoint.&nbsp; No success so far.</p>\r\n<p>From meetings with commentators on ILM, added in several clarifying comments, and received several additional Data Mgmt comments.&nbsp; Added them in, sent to Ms. Bowers for final review.&nbsp; On acceptance, will do a final version, adjust spacing, grammar check, etc and finalize graphics.</p>\r\n<p>Began working on&nbsp;a briefing&nbsp;presentation for staff on ILM, that can also be used for the staff trip to Denver.&nbsp; Needs to be delivered prior to 8/13.</p>\r\n<p>Began working with Mr. Stingley on the FDCCI plan for next year.</p>\r\n<p>Received verification of NOC power question, raised previous week.&nbsp;ICW FDCCI reporting.&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Submitted (hopefully) final draft version of ILM.&nbsp; Need one more minor spin to correct spacing, cut in newly revised graphics.</p>',	'<p>Met with DOI FDCCI team (telecon)&nbsp;for final&nbsp;review of the submission to OMB.&nbsp; No changes, no controversy.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Ms. Bowers and representatives from several other divisions to review comments to ILM, including reps from WO590,550.200,NOC.&nbsp; Got some useful clarificaiton on some comments that I have incorporated into the ILM.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mr. Samuels &amp; Mr. Stingley, re: role of 570 vs NOC in doing FDCCI planning.&nbsp; In the collective judgement, 570 does the DOI response on behalf of ADIRM, NOC PM does actual project plans.&nbsp; Began working with Mr. Stingley on editing last year\'s Plan.</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mr. Samuels, Ms. Bowers, Ms Hawkinson on the role of Data Managment activities in the ILM decided to do some expansion and add DM into the overall ILM graphic.&nbsp; Have incorporated the changes and done a semi final version of ILM for review.</p>\r\n<p>Sole BLM FDCCI team member on weekly DOI call.&nbsp; Important call--new GAO report requires surnamed response by next Friday. Notified Mr. Samuels, who had apparently not been notified of the requirement.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-03 17:11:05',	4,	'2012-08-10 13:54:10'),
(74,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-08-03',	'<p><span>Completed fingerprinting for the security badge by going to the main interior building on 7/30/12.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Finished reading the&nbsp;Integrated Lifecycle Management (ILM) document.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Met with Mohammad and Al\'Tariq to discuss activities and projects that I will be working on.</span></p>',	'<p><span>None</span></p>',	'<p><span>Attended the bi-weekly staff meeting and introduced myself to the team on 8/1/2012.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Met with Mohammad Haniffa to discuss department structure and how WO-570 fits in the DOI and IRM.&nbsp; Discussed what projects Mohammad is working and who are the stakeholders in the projects.&nbsp; He also discussed lesson learns from his experience.</span></p>\r\n<p><span><span>Held a meeting with Al&rsquo;Tariq and Mohammad to discuss activities I will be working on.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;Informed I will</span>&nbsp;be working on WO-200 IT portfolio management projects helping Mohammad.&nbsp; Mohammad will start adding me in the e-mail loop which is expected to start in week of 8/10/2012.</span></span></p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-06 09:10:36',	4,	'2012-08-13 10:08:51'),
(75,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-08-10',	'<p>Worked with Mr. Stingley doing further planning for data center closures.&nbsp; We had considerable consternation about the number of centers scheduled to close (27) in FY\'13&nbsp;and the fact that the NOC was not prepared, had done no planning or preparation, so escalated the matter . Our plan was negotiated last year and basically matched the M4E (Management for Excellence/Data Center Consolidation) plan that was underway.&nbsp; Found out&nbsp;this week that funding for&nbsp;M4E ($10M)&nbsp;was withdrawn last year, ergo no further consolidation/closing work&nbsp;was done by NOC.</p>\r\n<p>it was later determined that we should call a halt to closures&nbsp;after the two sites currently scheduled for closure in 1Q.&nbsp; The cloud initiative contract is about to be set (within the next few months), so the NOC really cannot plan for moving to cloud <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">or</span> NOC until we know what the cloud contract offers; so we will promise DOI/OMB&nbsp;to do a mid-year update once we know what path&nbsp;we will&nbsp;follow.</p>\r\n<p>I will put in considerable time on the FDCCI plan next week when the office is in Denver.</p>',	'<p>Early in the week, finalized an ILM&nbsp;draft for release to stakeholders containing comments from last week\'s meeting. Stakeholders were&nbsp;advised they had two weeks for final comments, after which the document was going to&nbsp;go for&nbsp;surnaming.</p>\r\n<p>Completed&nbsp;another draft of the ILM after discovery of a problem in the way NOC pm\'s were described.&nbsp; Fixed the problem (which carried through&nbsp;nearly a&nbsp;dozen sections of the document), and did a final polishing (spacing, spell/grammar check, etc.).&nbsp; I expect further revisions after the Denver meetings</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Held briefing for 570, 550, 590&nbsp;staff going to Denver, as ILM is a topic of discussion with the NOC.&nbsp; Got a few good comments, rolled the changes into the second draft described above.</p>\r\n<p>Met w/ Mr. Samuels, Mr. Stingley and Ms. Jollay (telecon) regarding the difficult status of Data Center Closings in prep for warning senior managment of the problem.&nbsp; Hopefully, the decision late Thursday to call a halt to closings will be accepted by DOI and will&nbsp;buy us some time.</p>\r\n<p>Attended Wed. DOI FDCCI Telecon, which included a webmeeting&nbsp;review of the TCO model.&nbsp; A Month back, contractors were absolutely&nbsp;forbidden to&nbsp;view the doc, I was once asked to leave a telecon with Mr. Samuels&nbsp;when they heard I was&nbsp;a contractor.&nbsp; Now they are saying to just&nbsp;have me sign&nbsp;a Bureau standard NDA. Haven\'t heard from anyone on that, yet, nor do I have a copy of the model yet.&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Need an NDA for access to the TCO model.&nbsp; We are under orders to use&nbsp;TCO as a part of our Savings Utilization Plan supplied by DOI, which must be submitted on 9/7 as part of out 2013 FDCCI Plan and I&nbsp;have been&nbsp;assigned to handle that portion of the SUP.</p>',	'<p>NDA?</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-10 16:10:07',	4,	'2012-08-16 11:19:23'),
(76,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-08-10',	'<p><span>Finished reviewing Integrated Lifecycle Management (ILM) and written comments regarding the document. I have given this document to Mohammad and Al\'Tariq.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Met with Naomi to discuss few projects I will be working on. I will be working on Mobility Strategy and Inventory of Mission Critical Business Processes and Application.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Attended a training session for the FISSA + Privacy &amp; Records Management which is required to get BLM network access.</span></p>',	'<p><span>Finished the computer based training for the FISSA + Privacy and Records Management training so I can get access to the BLM network.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Created a document with my comments requested by Mohammad regarding Integrated Lifecycle Management (ILM).</span></p>',	'<p><span>Met with Naomi Bowers and Kerry Lewis regarding new assignments. I will be creating a new mobility strategy for BLM and will be analyzing Inventory of Mission Critical Business Processes and application. I will need the network access which is expected in the week of 8/13/2012.</span></p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-13 09:39:42',	4,	'2012-08-16 11:30:06'),
(77,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-08-17',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I started to work on the Mobility strategy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I reviewed the Forrester Research Presentation and tried to understand what&rsquo;s needed to finish the mobility strategy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Al&rsquo;Tariq and I will be meeting with Forrester Research&rsquo;s account manager next week to discuss what we need from the Forrester&nbsp;so we can further in this project.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I am also working on the BLM Mission Critical Business application data collection project.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I contacted Dario Lunardi from New Mexico office to discuss how to get data from the application so I can start doing data analysis.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I was informed that the data call would be ending on September 5, 2012 and I would be receiving the data at the conclusion.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">I started to review Capital Planning and Investment Control (CPIC) handbook after meeting with Helen and Sayed WO-550 group. </span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Mobility Strategy Project - Create a list of items needed to finish Mobility strategy.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Mission Critical Business Application Project &ndash; Contacted the developer to get data so I can start analyzing the data for a report.</span></span></span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">I had a teleconference with Dario Lunardi from New Mexico to discuss Mission Critical Business application data call and status of the project.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Dario would be contacting the developer of the application to get data so I can start analyzing the data.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Met with Kerry Lewis to discuss Mobility strategy for iPads and get the ideas on how to craft a mobility strategy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Based on the discussion, we need to get some more information from Forrester before we can proceed further on this project.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Met with Sayed and Helen from WO-550 to get an overview of the CPIC process and how a Project Manager is involved in the CPIC process.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-13 09:52:57',	4,	'2012-08-21 12:43:57'),
(78,	14,	8,	1,	'2012-08-10',	'<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">AFMSS II APD - Worked on the overall acquisition plan and finalizing estimated cost for the APD processing functionality. The startup costs including the initial data work was an estimated cost of $80K for a total of $430K. However, I have not received a justification for the $490K in development cost.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Worked on modifications to the IPT Charter as directed by ITIB directive.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">MDT - We (MDT Team) have been working on a consolidated purchase for California, Oregon and Arizona and believed we were headed in the right direction and were going to be able to do a consolidated buy through Arizona. (Approximately $250,000.00 jointly). <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>This acquisition will provide the LEO/Field Going Agents the MDT devices required for the CAD and IMARS connectivity.</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">BLM IT Portfolio -<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>reviewed the &ldquo;Integrated review process&rdquo; that was submitted in 2010.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The process was briefly discussed and improvements and enhancements were highlighted.</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</span></span></p>',	'<p>AFMSS II APD - Submitted briefing presentation to Acting AD for IRM surrounding complications with the IPT Charter and RFP activity being non-compliant to ITIB directive for planning and acquisitions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MDT - The National MDT Team has completed the following task:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">1)<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The National MDT Team has identified the necessary hardware requirements and configurations and manufacturer.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">2)<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The National MDT Team and the Arizona IT Staff have identified a potential vendor and cost estimate.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">3)<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The National MDT Team and the Arizona IT Staff have obtained approval for this acquisition from the WO - Division of IT Investment Management</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">4)<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The Arizona Purchasing / Contracting Staff has broken out the Purchase Requisitions by State and has entered them into FBMS.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">5)<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Funding and funding codes for this acquisition were identified by staff in Oregon and provided to the team and have been entered with the PR.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II APD - Conducted the first IPT meeting 8/6/2012</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Conference call (MDT Team) 8/7/2012</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">AFMSS II APD - Cost projections have not been validated.&nbsp; The RFP activities are not in compliance with ITIB directive.&nbsp; IPT Charter is non-compliant to ITIB directive.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MDT - Can\'t acquire all state MDT devices via one contracting vehicle.</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">AFMSS II APD - Cost projections have not been validated.&nbsp; The RFP activities are not in compliance with ITIB directive.&nbsp; IPT Charter is non-compliant to ITIB directive.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MDT - Can\'t acquire all state MDT devices via one contracting vehicle.</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-14 10:20:38',	4,	'2012-08-16 11:31:35'),
(79,	14,	8,	1,	'2012-08-03',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">AFMSS II APD - Worked on the overall acquisition plan and&nbsp;finalizing estimated cost for the APD processing functionality. The startup costs including the initial data work was an estimated cost of $80K for a total of $430K. However, I have not received a justification for the $490K in development cost.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MDT - Worked to resolve issues surrounding MDT device orders for all state LEO\'s and Field Going Agents associated with the CAD/MDT project.&nbsp; The problem is procurementcannot buy all the product for all the states.&nbsp; Each state must do their own or the NOC has to do it.&nbsp; The issue is the property assets in FBMS.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">BLM&nbsp;IT Portfolio -&nbsp;&nbsp;reviewed <span style=\"color: #1f497d;\">the &ldquo;Integrated review process&rdquo; that was&nbsp;submitted in 2010.&nbsp; The process was briefly discussed and improvements and enhancements were highlighted.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #1f497d;\">Tablet PC - work remote desktop solution for law enforcement and remote workers.</span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">AFMSS II APD - Submitted a revised acquisition strategy draft the AFMSS APD team.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MDT -</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">BLM&nbsp;IT Portfolio -&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #1f497d;\">Tablet PC - </span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MDT - Bi-Weekly Law Enforcement Meeting 7/30/2012</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">BLM&nbsp;IT Portfolio -&nbsp;&nbsp;Team Meeting 7/31/2012</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">AFMSS II APD - Cost projections have not been validated.&nbsp; The RFP activities are not in compliance with ITIB directive.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MDT - Can\'t acquire all state MDT devices via one contracting vehicle.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #1f497d;\">Tablet PC - Still can\'t acquire iPhones.</span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">AFMSS II APD - Cost projections have not been validated.&nbsp; The RFP activities are not in compliance with ITIB directive.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">MDT - Can\'t acquire all state MDT devices via one contracting vehicle.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #1f497d;\">Tablet PC - Need assistance in getting a contracting vehicle in place to acquire iPhones.</span></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-14 10:21:55',	14,	'2012-08-16 11:09:57'),
(80,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-08-17',	'<p>Began working on Annual edit/rewrite of FDCCI Plan for FY2013.&nbsp; We were informed last week in the weekly conference call that we would need to supply several new sections, including a power metering plan, and a Savings Utilization Plan that would be driven by the OMB TCO model.&nbsp; Knowing contractors were prevented from reviewing this model without an NDA, 570 personnel contacted appropriate reps to have the NDA generated.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>. Data Entry seems dubious in some places (we have 51 data centers, closing 47...they show 40). Unfortunately, key 570 personnel are now in training.&nbsp; Will wait for NOC PM to return from leave Tuesday, then schedule a meeting with DOI PMs to review the model.</p>\r\n<p>Began editing new OMB FDCCI Template editing, planning , cutting/pasting appropriate sections from previous plan into the new model.&nbsp; The good news is that they place strict page limits on each section, so main job is editing last year\'s plan&nbsp;(removing information)&nbsp;and updating with current information.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Continued working with CA State Office on their closure documentation.&nbsp; They are completely unlike Oregon (More like the state office, which will remain open). CA has moved from its data center into shared space with BOR, thus CASO can register as closed...but all of their apps must be reported in ADAT, so there has been confusion all around.&nbsp; Believe clarification will finally happen next week.</p>',	'<p>Nothing finalized.</p>',	'<p>In the Wed. conference call this week, received word that an entirely new template was forthcoming from OMB, that specified format for the annual replanning.&nbsp; Received the template, including the sections that involve the TCO model.&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-20 12:11:18',	4,	'2012-08-26 19:57:13'),
(81,	18,	12,	1,	'2012-08-10',	'<p>Prepared template design set-up and&nbsp;utilizing and reworking some of the old BLM template parts.</p>\r\n<p>Created style sheets for all the formatting pieces/parts that would be in the book, (like for the 6 indent formatting parts, text table parts, bolds, italics, bold italics, subheads, main heads, etc)</p>\r\n<p>Created a table of contents.</p>\r\n<p>Printed out the 105 page word document.</p>\r\n<p>Created and paginated all the text table charts in advance, for dropping in later, while paginating the copy.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Started on ILM book project.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	2,	2,	'2012-08-23 13:38:40',	NULL,	'2012-09-04 10:39:31'),
(82,	18,	12,	1,	'2012-08-17',	'<p>Extracted all the artwork graphs out of the ILM word document.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Adjusted them all to cmyk tifs, then greyscale tifs, 300 DPI resolution in Photoshop. Also fixed some elements on the these graphs to make them better.</p>\r\n<p>Created 1 graph from scratch in Quark, because the graph in the Word document, was too dark and unreadable.</p>\r\n<p>Flowed in the copy from the Word document in the Quark document and then started to do the pagination utilizing the style sheets that I had already created during the template prep period.</p>\r\n<p>Adjusted some of the style sheets as needed during the pagination process. Also had to adjust some of the text table charts to fit in the flow of the pagination process.</p>\r\n<p>Created a title and copyright page. Added in all the appropriated page numbers to the TOC topics.</p>\r\n<p>Did a spell check on the Quark document after the pagination process was complete.</p>\r\n<p>Did a find and change for the word \"Lifecycle\" as it was spelled as one word and also as two throughout the given word document and fixed all those instances.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed the whole formatting with guides on and guides off to make sure that nothing was missed or left out or in properly spaced or other formatting issues that needed to be adjusted.</p>\r\n<p>Researched online in the BLM website and other sites until I found great photos for cover photos for the front and back covers.</p>\r\n<p>Also researched for high quality BLM logo and IRM logos. Downloaded them and adjusted them in Photoshop.</p>\r\n<p>Downloaded over 20 high resolution photos from the website.&nbsp;Adjusted those photos in Photoshop, to cmyk and tifs and changed their sizes.</p>\r\n<p>Created a front and back cover template in photoshop, placed and adjusted those photos to fix the spaces in the template. Typed in copy for the front and back covers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Placed these covers into the Quark document.</p>\r\n<p>Reviewed the whole entire book 1 more time and then make a PDF and uploaded it to the Atechra website for Kerry Lewis to have for proofing on August 16th.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Finished pagination of the interior of the book, for the first round for first proof.</p>\r\n<p>Also created front and back covers.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	2,	1,	'2012-08-23 13:56:47',	NULL,	'2012-09-03 14:02:39'),
(83,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-08-24',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Had a series of discussion meetings with Forrester (e-mail and Face-to-Face) to define Mobility Strategy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I would define a path forward on how to create a draft version.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>My account is now set up with Forrester so I have access to research papers from Forrester.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Will set up a meeting with Forrester Analyst to get some ideas for the Mobility Strategy.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Received the partial data for the Mission Critical Business (MCB) application data call.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Data call&rsquo;s deadline is September 5<sup>th</sup>.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Started analyzing initial data and gave summary to Al&rsquo;Tariq.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Need to discuss this data analysis with Forrester to see what they can help with the data call.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Reviewed Capital Planning and Investment Control (CPIC) handbook to discuss Project Manager&rsquo;s role with Sayed from CPIC group.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Mission Critical Business Application Project - I have finished initial analysis of Mission Critical Business (MCB) data call and showed to Al&rsquo;Tariq.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>This analysis was based on partial data since data call won&rsquo;t be finished until September 5<sup>th</sup>.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I will be working on this data analysis for next few weeks.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Mobility Strategy Project - Had my account set up with Forrester so I can access research papers for the Mobility Strategy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Met with Al\'Tariq to get detail information about Mobility Strategy project and BLM Mission Critical Business Application data call analytics.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>For Mobility Strategy, I need to work with Forrester Research analyst to get more detail about the work they have done and start the ground work with the team.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>For Mission Critical Business data call, I need to analyze data so when data call is finished, we can summarize all the data.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Held a face-to-face meeting with Nami Wadhawan, from Forrester Research, along with Al&rsquo;Tariq to discuss going forward path for Mobility Strategy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>We had a very good path forward discussion for the Mobility Strategy and data analysis for the Mission Critical Business Application.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I will be working with Simon Yates, an analyst from Forrester.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Had a teleconference meeting with Mike Thomas from Forrester Research to get an overview of services Forrester is offering.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I had my account set up with Forrester website for reviewing research papers.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-24 16:01:42',	4,	'2012-08-29 18:04:04'),
(84,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-08-24',	'<p>Entire week spent on FDCCI.</p>\r\n<p>Generated new draft of the annual Closure&nbsp;Plan based upon the OMB template distributed last week.&nbsp; Required significant editing to shoehorn our document into their format, with page limits.&nbsp; Also requires templates for reporting data center closure progress, which requires detailed summary and planning efforts, and requires assumptions that must be vetted when Mr. Stingley returns next week&nbsp;.</p>',	'<p>New draft closure plan.</p>',	'<p>Weekly FDCCI conference; no major announcements or activities to report; most attendees seem not to have even looked at the TCO and Planning templates distributed last week.&nbsp; New plan due 9/7/12</p>\r\n<p>Met with Roger Franklin (telecon) and Alex Torres (BLM PM)&nbsp;regarding the TCO model.&nbsp; It is an extremely complex document.&nbsp;Our&nbsp;2012 inventory data was entered automatically, but the model does not report it back accurately.&nbsp; Will need to have further discussions about how to proceed.</p>\r\n<p>Met briefly with Oregon data owner re 4Q&nbsp;closure docs.&nbsp; Realized we need a point of clarification regarding telecom costs (weekly call last week directed us to NOT report telecom in any form).&nbsp; We did so last qtr and were about to do so again (I supplied the docs to Oregon in July.)&nbsp; Sent note to Mr. Franklin asking clarification.</p>',	'<p>TCO model.&nbsp; (We\'ll get it resolved next week).</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-24 16:39:05',	13,	'2012-08-31 20:30:32'),
(85,	18,	12,	1,	'2012-08-24',	'<p>No activities this week, awaiting for changes to come back from the PDF proof.</p>',	'<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Times; font-size: 24px; line-height: normal;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-attachment: initial; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #555555; line-height: 1.2em; background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(images/body_bg.jpeg); height: 100%; background-position: initial initial; margin: 8px;\">\r\n<p>No accomplishments this week, awaiting for changes to come back from the PDF proof.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</span></p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	1,	18,	'2012-08-24 16:58:36',	NULL,	'2012-08-24 16:58:47'),
(86,	18,	12,	1,	'2012-08-31',	'<p>None. Awaiting for changes for the ILM book to come.</p>',	'<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Times; font-size: 24px; line-height: normal;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-attachment: initial; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #555555; line-height: 1.2em; background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(images/body_bg.jpeg); height: 100%; background-position: initial initial; margin: 8px;\">\r\n<p>None.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</span></p>',	'<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Times; font-size: 24px; line-height: normal;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-attachment: initial; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #555555; line-height: 1.2em; background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(images/body_bg.jpeg); height: 100%; background-position: initial initial; margin: 8px;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Times; font-size: 24px; line-height: normal;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-attachment: initial; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #555555; line-height: 1.2em; background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(images/body_bg.jpeg); height: 100%; margin: 8px;\">\r\n<p>None.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</span></p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	2,	2,	'2012-08-31 14:09:43',	NULL,	'2012-09-18 12:29:54'),
(87,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-08-31',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Reviewed DoD mobile strategy document, CIO Council&rsquo;s report on BYOD guidelines and other documents to get ideas of other agencies&rsquo; approach for mobility strategy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Started working on Mobility Strategy after getting clear direction from Al&rsquo;Tariq and Naomi.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I have started to work on the draft version.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Performed more analysis on the data collected from data call for BLM Mission Critical Business application.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Has asked Chris to provide latest snapshot of data since Wyoming has finished the data call.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I will show the full analysis after I get data from Chris.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; color: #000000; font-family: Calibri;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">BLM Mission Critical Application &ndash; Created a pivot table to show data multiple way.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Mobility Strategy project &ndash; After reading research papers on Mobility, started to write mobility strategy.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Met with Naomi earlier in the week to show her the status of Mobility Strategy and Mission Critical Business Application data collection.&nbsp; Outcome of this meeting was to continue work on creating a draft for mobility strategy and keep analyzing data for Mission Critical Business Application.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Attended a staff meeting for WO-570 to give status of the projects I have been working on.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Had a conference call with Forrester Research analyst Simon Yates and Nami for Mobility Strategy next steps and get some background information about Forrester&rsquo;s work so far and come up with next steps on how to tackle this project.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Nami would summarize next steps and send an e-mail.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-31 14:35:31',	16,	'2012-09-05 17:43:27'),
(88,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-08-31',	'<p>After a period of confusion regarding the TCO model, we received word Wednesday that we could supply our own modified version.&nbsp; Spent much of the remaining time building a new model based on the standard model Mr. Stingley developed for the individual site closings.</p>\r\n<p>Worked with Mr. Stingley on bringing the FY2013 plan to order.&nbsp; Nearing completion, with polishing next week &nbsp;and submission&nbsp;on 9/7.&nbsp; Action plan in place to finish out the week.</p>\r\n<p>Outlined several NOC/570 activities that need to be performed during the 6 Mo.&nbsp;data center closure hiatus that begins 10/1.&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Created new cost model for BLM Data Center Closings.</p>',	'<p>Weekly phone conference with DOI made a breakthrough regarding cost modeling; permitted to create&nbsp;a BLM cost&nbsp;document representing Bureau view of reality.</p>\r\n<p>Mr. Stingley &amp; I briefed Mr. Samuels on new strategies in the plan, including the new six-month hiatus from Data Center closures while we wait for the Cloud contract to be let.&nbsp; (It is not possible to plan to move to the cloud until we actually know what the contract offers, e.g. whether it has CASE tools or is pure IAAS).&nbsp; Similarly, it is not reasonable to plan to move everthing to the NOC when we know Cloud First is an important driver.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-08-31 15:06:40',	NULL,	'2012-09-05 17:45:17'),
(89,	2,	8,	1,	'2012-08-17',	'<p>AFMSS II - Worked on AFMSS II project milestones to the meet the following targets.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The scheduled milestones:</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">COB August 16 (this Thursday) selection of TECP members with concurrence of the IPT.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">COB August 17 (this Friday) complete changes and comments to the draft RFP on the SharePoint site. IPT members (not managers or advisors) indicate concurrence with the RFP (need concurrence from TECP members not on the IPT). If you want to see the final product before giving your concurrence then indicate your areas of concern and ensure you are available Monday afternoon. Also need all attachments for the reference web site.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Monday, August 20 I will address all the track changes and comments. It would be helpful if people were available for questions and clarifications as needed.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">COB Monday, August 20, submit finished package to Kim. Kim will finalize and get the peer review.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">COB Friday, August 24 Kim will post the RFP and Michelle will open the reference web site.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">RFP open until COB Monday, Sept 24. During this time we will need to be ready to respond to questions submitted via Kim. Members of the team will also update planning documents to reflect the current status and timing of the project with concurrence of the entire team. Kim will commit the FY2012 funding to the project before FBMS goes down.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Friday, Sept 28, Kim provides packages to TECP.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Wednesday, October 10, TECP selects winning proposal. Although current plan does not include presentations by bidders, this time frame would allow presentations by top 2 or 3 bids if needed.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia;\">Monday, October 15, award contract.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC - Worked with Oregon State Office to get law enforcement tablets configured with the correct apps to meet mission needs.&nbsp; Worked with NIFC to ensure law&nbsp;enforcement tablets were configured with the correct law enforcement specific productivity apps.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Worked on completion of the RFP through FWS IDIQ.</p>\r\n<p>NDA - Developed non-disclosure agreement between Atechra Contractors and BLM.</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II - Completed the changes to the AFMSS II RFP.&nbsp; Completed the draft AFMSS II IPT Charter.</p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC -&nbsp;Completed Oregon State Office law enforcement tablets configuration.&nbsp; Completed NIFC law enforcement tablets configurations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Completed all WO-570 requirements to ensure issuance of the CAD/MDT Law Enforcement Network RFP.</p>\r\n<p>NDA - Completed non-disclosure agreement between Atechra Contractors and BLM.&nbsp; Delivered signed copies for all Atechra Staff assigned to the BLM to the BLM COR.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II -&nbsp; AFMSS IPT Meeting\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nTABLET PC - Numerous phone calls with Tablet PC Project Leads.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - BI-weekly Law Enforcement Meeting</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II -&nbsp; None</p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC - Contracting to deliver requested devices.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Delay in RFP.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II -&nbsp; None</p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC - COR is aware of device acquisition concerns.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Delay in RFP.</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-04 10:42:02',	2,	'2012-09-05 17:41:47'),
(90,	2,	8,	1,	'2012-08-24',	'<p>AFMSS II - Worked on AFMSS II comments and changes to the IPT Charter. Worked on&nbsp;comments and changes to RFP.&nbsp; Worked on security compliance documentation for the RFP.<br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><br />TABLET PC -&nbsp;Day to day operations and management of the tablet pc pilot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NLSS -&nbsp;Started reviewing the project management plan and requirements documentation.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Worked on RFP issuance.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II - Finalized AFMSS II&nbsp;RFP.&nbsp; Although the IPT Charter was finalized, I still have concerns with the document. Validated AFMSS APD Module costing $490K</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>',	'<p>AFMSS II -&nbsp;IPT Charter and RFP Finalization Meeting.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><br />TABLET PC - Numerous calls with Project Leads.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II - Not in agreement with IPT Charter roles and responsibilities.<br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><br />TABLET PC - None.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - Delay in RFP issuance.</p>\r\n<p>NLSS -&nbsp;None.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II -&nbsp;COR is aware.</p>\r\n<p>TABLET PC - None.</p>\r\n<p>MDT - COR is aware.</p>\r\n<p>NLSS -&nbsp;None.</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-04 10:43:37',	2,	'2012-09-05 17:40:56'),
