(95,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-09-14',	'<p><span>In the early part of the week, I worked on the Mobility Strategy draft requested by Naomi.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I have also added many sections to the draft version.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Initial draft was given to Naomi on-time.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Naomi has reviewed the draft and suggested a&nbsp;few improvement ideas.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Next step is that I will review those improvement ideas and update the draft.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span>For Mission Critical Business (MCB) project, I have analyzed new data for Mission Critical Business (MCB) application per request from BLM team to kick start the core team meeting.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I presented data analysis to the core MCB project team and they liked what I have done so far.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>The next step is to clean-up the data so more analysis can be performed.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>I will be working&nbsp;with the data clean up team&nbsp;for the&nbsp;next couple of weeks and will suggest what needs to be done.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p><span>In order to find some analyzing tool for MCB project data, I am working with Christine Hawkinson.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>IT service has installed Data Flux tool on our computers for the analysis.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>We are still in the early stage of this analysis using Data Flux.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><span>Federal Mobility Strategy &ndash; Draft version of Mobility Strategy was given to Naomi on-time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Mission Critical Business (MCB) Project &ndash; Draft version of analysis was shown to the MCB core team in the meeting.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Data Flux is installed&nbsp;on my computer.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><span>Attended a staff meeting of WO-570 to discuss and give update on current project status.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>I presented initial analysis and next steps for the MCB data analysis project to the MCB core team meeting called by Mr. Al&rsquo;Tariq Samuels.</span></p>',	'<p><span>n/a</span></p>',	'<p><span>n/a</span></p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-14 15:55:16',	4,	'2012-09-20 11:58:26'),
(96,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-09-14',	'<p><span>Finalized the FY2013 Federal Data Center Closing Initiative (FDCCI) Plan for BLM with a couple of minor adjustments. Mon,Tues.&nbsp;Final version&nbsp;sent for signature Tuesday.&nbsp; Plan calls for a six month hiatus for closings, to allow the cloud contract to be&nbsp;sent and give us a bit of time to plan for moving to cloud storage.&nbsp; Contract scheduled to be available by end of FY Q1,2013.&nbsp; In the meantime much planning ADAT runs, and engineering design must be accomplished.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>At Mr. Stingley\'s request, drafted IM\'s for NOC to proceed with six areas of work during interim: 1)Run ADAT Scans on all software (DOI mandate by 12/31/12); 2)Architect/Engineer an enterpise-scale GIS solution; 3)&nbsp;Develop plan for virtualizing closing data centers in the cloud; 4) develop plan for implementing site closures at NOC if Cloud solution that is contracted for does not match BLM\'s needs; 5) Develop overall storage solution; 6) Develop plan for National Applications in a \"to be\" environment; 7)Complete SOP for states for ADAT runs.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>At Mr. Samuels\' request, began preparation of a presentation for management describing the challenges we face in closing this many data centers...47 of 95 Bureau-Wide.&nbsp; Drafted initial overview sections, Mr. Stingley detailed each of the IM efforts; cut the two together, reviewed with Al\' Tariq and Pat, made edits, Al\' Tariq will set meetings next week.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Much back-and-forth with Alex Torres (DCCI PM) about finalizing last six Oregon sites. We seem to be in agreement, but Oregon SIRMO applied incorrect numbers to cost model; he is on travel for much of this week; may have to postpone until his return; does not jeopardize closure by 9/28, date&nbsp;committed to&nbsp;in plan.&nbsp;</span></p>',	'<p><span>Completed 2014 FDCCI Plan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Completed presentation for ADIR &amp; head of NOC (Ruth Welch)</span></p>',	'<p><span>Weekly FDCCI phone conference.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Met with Mr Samuels and Stingley, to edit FDCCI Challenges presentation.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Met with NOC/570 team members to begin reworking ILM, subsequent to the Denver meeting.&nbsp; Ms. Bowers and Gail Colbert from the NOC were tasked as team leaders; Alex Torres is other member.&nbsp; Initial call involved setting some high level goals to identify roles &amp; responsibilities, some process elements, some discussion regarding implementation of ILM vis a&rsquo; vis the states.&nbsp; Determined that we will meet weekly until we reach resolution.</p>\r\n</span></p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-17 10:52:07',	4,	'2012-09-20 11:42:59'),
(97,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-09-21',	'<p>Spent considerable time reviewing the TCO model to identify further error points; discovered that there is one section where only 3 of 47 sites were loaded into the model;&nbsp; Will transmit findings to FDCCI PMO for relay on to OMB.</p>\r\n<p>Finalized Oregon closing documents including discovery of an error I had made in one, which resulted in considerable discussion of reporting strategy.&nbsp; Original 2010 baseline for&nbsp;Eugene&nbsp;showed them with 13 servers. By the 2011 data call they had reduced to 3.&nbsp; Previously we had used the 2011 call as the operative baseline, but I raised the question that shouldn\'t we get credit for one site that didn\'t result in additional costs? Finally determined that precedent was more important and reported as we had previously, 2011 numbers.</p>',	'<p>Delivered completed Closing Documents for six Oregon FDCCI sites, including transmittal letters and copies of the actual documents to all interested parties at NOC and in 570.&nbsp; This totals 15 site closures for the fiscal year and is in precise alignment with the plan submitted in 2011.</p>\r\n<p>Finalized FDCCI presentation, raising numerous strategic issues.&nbsp; We have taken the position that we cannot plan either a cloud move or a NOC move, until we know what services will be available under the DOI cloud contract.&nbsp; Contract will not be available before Jan.2013.&nbsp; Have declared a six-month hiatus on data center closures while we run ADAT scans by 12/31&nbsp;and plan for cloud contract.</p>\r\n<p>Completed second draft of IM for NOC to follow over next six months. ADAT scans, designing Enterpise GIS Solution, designing Enterprise storage solution, planning for services that will move to the NOC, and for&nbsp;services that move to the cloud,detailed plans for actually achieving site closures.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Met with Mr. Samuels, Mr. Stingley, Ms Jollay (570 ADIR)&nbsp;and Ms.Ruth Brown (NOC Director) regarding support for NOC on data center closures.&nbsp; Daunting task, BLM is committed to consolidating half of the total&nbsp;for DOI (47 of 95).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Met with Mr. Samuels and PM team regarding new assignments. I will be working with portfolio manager Naomi Bowers and have been assigned several&nbsp;projects.&nbsp; Initial tasking is to uncover whatever information is available internally, to develop current status on each project.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thus far there seems to be limited information&nbsp;in-house, may need to be gleaned from the business area.&nbsp; We are assigned to support WO300,500,700, GLO and ALIS.</p>\r\n<p>Phone meeting with Mr. Stingley, Oregon IT director Lloyd Gilham, NOC PMs, to finalize the Oregon closure&nbsp;documents.</p>\r\n<p>Telecon with NOC and state IT execs regarding the ADAT scans that need to be completed by 12/31/12 per DOI CIO.&nbsp; Considerable confusion exists about what an application is and how to report them, e.g. ARCGIS may have 100 components which could be considered as individual apps; in that particular instance, CTO has taken the position that ARCGIS is the app, but others confusions will remain.</p>\r\n<p>Weekly FDCCI conference call was short and anticlimactic, focused primarily on the DOI report to OMB summarizing the overall department plan.</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-21 15:18:59',	4,	'2012-09-26 15:12:16'),
(98,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-09-21',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">For Mission Critical Business (MCB) project, I had a meeting to discuss data cleanup.&nbsp; We had a very productive meeting and came up with good ideas.&nbsp; I summarized the meeting minutes and sent to the team.&nbsp; I have taken a&nbsp;few action items which I have finished some and continue to work some others.&nbsp; Data cleanup team is going to rely heavily on the objective team which will provide the guidance and objective.&nbsp; I will be working in the data clean up team in next couple of weeks and will continue to provide my expertise to achieve objectives of the data call. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">I have updated a draft version of the Mobility Strategy based on feedback from Naomi.&nbsp; Based on discussion with Al&rsquo;Tariq on Friday (9/21), this project will be taken over by Pat Stingley.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Al&rsquo;Tariq called a meeting to discuss future projects assignments.&nbsp; I will be helping Mohammad on SPATS, RMIS, PRIS, ESRS, FORVIS, WHBPS and NSN projects.&nbsp; I will be meeting with Mohammad&nbsp;to start&nbsp; reviewing each project next week.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Federal Mobility Strategy &ndash; Updated draft version based on Naomi&rsquo;s feedback.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Mission Critical Business (MCB) Project &ndash; Draft version of analysis was shown to the MCB core team in the meeting.&nbsp; Data Flux is installed&nbsp;on my computer.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Data cleanup discussion meeting &ndash; Lead a meeting to discuss what data we would need cleaned up and how to proceed further for the data analysis for Mission critical business project.&nbsp; We will be meeting early next week to discuss further actions needed to finish this project.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Objectives Discussion meeting &ndash; Attended this meeting to get assessment of the objective of Mission critical business team.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">BLM Portfolio meeting &ndash; Attended meeting called by Al&rsquo;Tariq Samuels to discuss future assignment for the WO-570 team.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-09-21 15:20:32',	4,	'2012-09-26 15:16:29'),
