(105,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-10-05',	'<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">I presented vendor selection business process which I crated based on my past experience to Mohammad.&nbsp; I presented Kepner-Tregoe methodology and AHP methodology for selection process.&nbsp; BLM uses similar technique to Kepner-Tregoe so Mohammad asked to present more information about AHP process. </span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">For Portfolio management, I started to look at the old documents regarding these projects.&nbsp; I will be meeting with Mohammad&nbsp;next week to discuss&nbsp;best ways to approach these projects.&nbsp; I have also gained access to EDMS so I can look at the old documents.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">For Mission Critical Business (MCB) project, I had presented action items from last meeting.&nbsp; Next step is to set up meeting next week with Data Cleanup team to define schedule for the data clean-up efforts.&nbsp; I also sent out the action items from the meeting.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Mission Critical Business (MCB) Project &ndash; Presented core team with data cleanup team summary and mockup charts.&nbsp; Next week, we will have&nbsp;another meeting to discuss next steps.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Vendor selection Business Process &ndash; Met with Mohammad to show what I have done for vendor selection business process.&nbsp; Next step is to have detailed process flow for selection process and more detailed information about AHP methodology.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Mission Critical Business Process meeting &ndash; Attend this meeting and presented Data Cleanup team&rsquo;s summary.</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Vendor Selection Business Process &ndash; Met face to face with Mohammad to discuss Vendor selection business process.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-10-05 15:18:46',	4,	'2012-10-08 18:17:17'),
(106,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-10-05',	'<p>Spent a fairly significant amount of the week redoing the latest version of the ILM, taking into account new Portfolio Management approach. &nbsp;In addition to a fair amount of editing, reviewed the CPIC handbook and borrowed a couple of significant additions, a section discussing Portfolio Management, and the Thresholds for when IT projects must be reviewed by ITIB. Also, what documentation obligations are incumbent on states when projects are below the thresholds.</p>\r\n<p>Consulted, via email, with Ms. Bowers and Mr. Naved on several aspects of ILM; beginning to work like a well-oiled team.</p>\r\n<p>Consulted w/Mr. Lewis about a lack I perceived in the ILM...there is no mention anywhere in the document of &nbsp;Conops. &nbsp;In my mind this is an important phase that should be included in most projects. &nbsp;Mr. lewis explained that there had, at one time, been a Concept of Operations in the document, and we were able to track down the version. Sometime between spring 2010 and summer 2011, the entire concept was removed. &nbsp;Mr. Lewis to approach Mr. Samuels for a ruling.</p>',	'<p>Completed a full edit on ILM. &nbsp;I had expected it would take most of two weeks, although there are a couple of outstanding issues, it only took about four days.</p>\r\n<p>After several email exchanges with Mr. Aslam, I finally got the key to working on the CPIC SharePoint site and found excellent, up-to-date information on the new projects I\'m responsible for and began reviewing.</p>',	'<p>Mr. Samuels was unavailable for our ILM team meeting last week, so Ms. Bowers, Mr. Naved and I briefed him on status. &nbsp; Agreed I would do another edit to take new changes into account, and he ruled on titles: Portfolio managers, not \"Investment\" managers.</p>\r\n<p>Weekly FDCCI call was inconsequential. &nbsp; Ironically, after driving the bureaus for months to get planning submissions in by 9/7 so the department would have time to get their plan in by 9/28, on the morning of 9/28, after putting on the finishing touches, OMB asked all departments to WAIT a month before submitting!&nbsp;FDCCI leads volunteered BLM for duty in coming up with a template in MS Project reporting of detailed schedules and plans for data center closures. Roger Franklin asked if they could start with Mr. Wilbur and&nbsp;I next week, I&nbsp;recommended it would be better to wait for Mr. Torres to return from leave as he does the actual closing planning.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-10-05 16:28:31',	4,	'2012-10-08 18:22:45'),
(107,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-10-12',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">I have been in the planning for meeting Division of Business and Technology alignment (WO-570) for two half-day sessions. &nbsp;We have defined activities for the portfolio management group for FY13.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">For Portfolio management project; started to review SharePoint link given by Mohammad for the Science permit application and tracking system (SPATS). &nbsp;I will be meeting with Mohammad next week to discuss further action plan for this project.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">For MCB project, I held a meeting to discuss deadline for data clean up efforts.&nbsp; We will be freezing MCB site by COB on Wednesday (10/17/2012).&nbsp; We will have all the data cleanup activity done by November 1<sup>st.</sup></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">For vendor selection criteria, I have&nbsp;found out more detail about Analytical Hierarchy Process (AHP) for Mohammad.&nbsp; I will show him my research next week.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For FY 2013, Portfolio team has defined the priority for the year.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For MCB project, finalized the deadline for the data cleanup activity schedule.&nbsp; Deadline is November 1st for&nbsp;all the data cleanup activities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For Portfolio management project, looked over documents for <span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Science permit application and tracking system (SPATS). &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attended WO-570 planning meeting for FY 2013.&nbsp; We have come up with the&nbsp;top three activities for Portfolio management team.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">For MCB project, I have called a meeting to discuss task needed to complete data cleanup efforts and finalized the deadline for these tasks.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-10-12 14:57:50',	4,	'2012-10-22 14:45:38'),
