(111,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-10-19',	'<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">For Portfolio management project, based on NOC&rsquo;s website about project status, I have started to create a summary table for the portfolio project I have been assigned.&nbsp; This table summarizes current status, next milestone and business and IT project manager for my projects.&nbsp; This information would be useful to find a quick status of all the projects.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Created a two page summary document for Mr. Al&rsquo;Tariq Samuels on Mission Critical Business Process (MCB).&nbsp; Need to review this document with Mr. Samuels next week so he can notify the status of MCB to field and district offices.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attended the Forrester&rsquo;s information session about our account with Forrester.&nbsp; They explained how we can use their services and how to access the research document from their website.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Met with Lou Eichenbaum, in his office, to discuss MCB&rsquo;s summary and status of the project.&nbsp; This information would be useful in the Asset Management project which he is heading.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For MCB project, I have created a two page summary of MCB project status for field and district office.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For Portfolio management project, I have started to create a summary table which shows project status and contact information.</p>',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attended Forrester Research information session to get more familiar with the Forrester&rsquo;s website and services.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">I showed the status and summary of MCB project to Lou so he can get ideas of what was collected in the MCB project.&nbsp; This information would be useful in Asset management project.</span></p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-10-19 14:43:27',	4,	'2012-10-24 17:15:49'),
(112,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-10-19',	'<p>Very quiet, nearly all FTE\'s out most of the week.&nbsp; Spent considerable time researching assigned projects.&nbsp; Produced a report&nbsp;comparing NOC customer dashboard, CPIC dashboard and 2013 budget portfolio and all other known projects (several of our assignments do not appear in any of these documents). Identified several funded projects not reported on NOC dashboard and having no assigned project manager.&nbsp; Three projects from CPIC dashboard assigned to WO 500 have no PM (although only one is funded). Some Funded projects do not appear on CPIC dashboard.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Assisted PM in sorting out a point of confusion in the annual FDCCI inventory.&nbsp;The Milwaukee Eastern States office has reported having two mainframe computers, no servers for each of the surveys.&nbsp; Seemed unlikely, but if true would probably require some engineering to close/consolidate site.&nbsp; Turned out to be false reporting.</p>',	'<p>Completed project comparison report and submitted to Mr. Samuels,&nbsp;for assistance in organizing&nbsp;the portfolio management&nbsp; organization.</p>',	'<p>Completed final review of 4Q FY \'12 data center closure documents with DOI Leads; discovered 1 small error in 1 doc; submitted corrected doc and 2012 is done, 15 closures, per commitment,&nbsp;on time,</p>\r\n<p>Weekly FDCCI call was non-eventful and short (20Min.)</p>\r\n<p>Participated in an initial call w/DOI leads&nbsp;about furnishing greater&nbsp;detail of site closure schedule/plans.&nbsp; OMB wants to see detailed schedules by site, esp. as the closure date approaches (mention made of weekly reporting!).&nbsp; Bureaus are not particularly in favor for a variety of reasons, but don\'t really want to express what they are...basic desire not to be micromanaged from afar.</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-10-19 16:11:45',	4,	'2012-10-24 17:12:38'),
(113,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-10-26',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Met with Mr. Al&rsquo;Tariq and Naomi to get feedback on my initial draft for Mission Critical Business Process Summary.&nbsp; Finalized a two page summary document for Mr. Al&rsquo;Tariq Samuels on Mission Critical Business Process (MCB) after getting feedback from Mr. Al&rsquo;Tariq and Naomi.&nbsp; Also, created a memo for BLM community for Summary and raw data.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attended the HP&rsquo;s project and portfolio management tool demo given by Melillo Consulting Company.&nbsp; This tool would be used by BLM for their Project and Portfolio management work.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">For Portfolio management project, based on NOC&rsquo;s website about project status, I have updated a summary table for the portfolio project I have been assigned.&nbsp; This table summarizes current status, next milestone and business and IT project manager for my projects.&nbsp; This information would be useful to find a quick status of all the projects.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attended a staff meeting of WO-570.&nbsp; I had given status of Portfolio management project status to Mohammad before attending the staff meeting.&nbsp; I had also given status report to Mohammad for his weekly report for Al&rsquo;Tariq.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">For MCB project, I have created a memorandum for BLM community for MCB status along with MCB status report for Al&rsquo;Tariq.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">For Portfolio management project, I had given status summary report to Mohammad on all the work I had done on Portfolio Management.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attended HP&rsquo;s Project and Portfolio tool demonstration meeting by Melillo Consulting Company.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Met with Al&rsquo;Tariq and Naomi to discuss summary report of MCB and get feedback.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-10-26 14:49:09',	4,	'2012-10-31 17:37:37'),
