(122,	13,	2,	1,	'2012-11-09',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Focused primarily on creating a Concept of Operations for the PPM Tool Implementation Project. &nbsp;Current ConOps template is extremely detailed and requires a substantial amount of researching and original writing. Actually seems a bit over-thought, asking fine shades of meaning and details of operation that are difficult in a concept document.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">Awaiting management review of two drafts of the Integrated Lifecycle Management framework, and the Mission Needs Statement and Charter for the PPM Tool Implementation.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">Struggled with implementation of Google Mail (along with everyone else in WO500 &amp; state IT operations). Switch generated hundreds of emails (I did X in Outlook...how do I do that in Google?). &nbsp;Approaches are substantially different in some ways, e.g. everything is \"search\" oriented in Google&hellip; You don\'t sort the inbox by originator, you search for all emails from that person.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Attended Application and Data Assessment Tool training for FDCCI. &nbsp; ADAT surveys are run on all applications on all servers to determine appropriateness of moving the app to the cloud. &nbsp;It has been a topic of intereste and confusion for months, and is still not totally clear.</p>\r\n<p>Also attended the other Google Training course. &nbsp;Pretty generic course, doesn\'t cover the look and feel of the DOI application.</p>',	'<p>The weekly Federal Data Center Consolidation Initiative conference call was uneventful.</p>\r\n<p>ADAT training was helpful, I think...more than a dozen people from BLM offices responsible for running ADAT surveys were in attendance, including Mike Smith of 570/580 who will handle WO server reports</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	1,	'2012-11-09 13:20:52',	13,	'2012-11-14 09:58:14'),
(123,	16,	2,	1,	'2012-11-09',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">For Project Portfolio project, I had continued to work on databases, middleware, Server OS, Web Server, Reporting tools and other tools for the project I am assigned to. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">I met with Chris Hawkinson to find out more information about which projects uses Geospatial application. &nbsp;It was a useful meeting to find out the status of each application from Geospatial point of view.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\">Based on my research from website and information from meeting with different people, I have created a draft version for Mohammad to review.&nbsp; Mohammad is reviewing this table and noting down some feedback so this can be a good table for future project portfolio work.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">As part of the bureau&rsquo;s move to Bison Connect, Department-wide email and calendar system, I had watched few videos for handling conversion from folder to labels.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">As for Mission critical business process project, Mr. Al&rsquo;Tariq Samuels had send out summary document for review and waiting for the feedback from the core team.&nbsp; Good news is that these data are being used for other projects within BLM.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Project Portfolio &ndash; Created a table of databases, middleware, Server OS, Web Server, Reporting tools, other tools, and Geospatial application list for Mohammad&rsquo;s review.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Mission Critical Process Project &ndash;Summary draft of initial data was sent out to core team by Mr. Al&rsquo;Tariq Samuels.&nbsp; We are waiting for the feedback from the core team.&nbsp; Based on this feedback, I will change&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Met with Chris Hawkinson to discuss which applications are using Geospatial application for project portfolio.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	1,	'2012-11-09 15:20:35',	16,	'2012-11-14 09:57:56'),
(124,	14,	8,	1,	'2012-11-09',	'<p>MDT - Working to get MDT RFP bids. &nbsp;Worked with Arizona on SIM card and 4GE LTE service for toughbooks configurations. Provided MDT supporting documentation for cost associated with MDT project.</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS II - Provided supporting documentation for cost associated wtih AFMSS Modules. &nbsp;Worked on validating WO-300 cost projections of the&nbsp;Processing Module (AISPQ)&nbsp;which is an automated industry submissions, processing, and queries module,&nbsp;Inspection &amp; Enforcement Module (AEII), and the Integrated&nbsp;Data Management Module (IDMI).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>AFMSS II - APD no activity required. &nbsp;RFP evaluations being conducted by government personnel.</p>\r\n<p>NLSS - Provided supporting documentation for cost associated will pilot application.</p>',	'<p>AFMSS II - Completed evaluations of AISPQ and IDMI modules costing. Cost projections, based my experiences, are largely overstated and more importantly can only be estimated at the completion of APD module based on the developmental dependencies. I concur with the WO-300 that the costing provided is overstated.</p>',	'<p>MDT - Meeting with WO-800 to project RFP completion activities and milestones/targets.</p>',	'<p>MDT - RFP still delayed.</p>',	'<p>MDT - RFP still delayed.</p>',	2,	1,	'2012-11-13 15:13:11',	2,	'2012-11-14 09:57:36'),
