(142,	16,	18,	6,	'2012-12-21',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">I have continued to work on the inventory database for the Project Portfolio Management implementation.&nbsp; Inventory list is a part of Acquire knowledge section for implementing the Project Portfolio at the BLM.&nbsp; The inventory database is almost complete and &nbsp;I will set up a meeting after the holidays to show inventory list to Mohammad and go forward from there.</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">This week, I had a teleconference with Neffra Mathews (NOC), Cory Black (Alaska) and Donna (Montana) to introduce myself as a project manager and discuss the status of the Science Permit Application and Tracking System (SPATS).&nbsp; We discussed future steps needed for this project.&nbsp; I will be calling a conference call after&nbsp;the&nbsp;holidays.&nbsp; SPATS team also showed me important documents which I will be reviewing next week to get up to speed on SPATS projects.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">I started to review Process flow and data model for the SPATS project which will help with future activity for this project.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Database for the entire BLM IT application is about 95% complete.&nbsp; I have manually removed the duplicates from the database.&nbsp; Next step is to review this database with Mohammad.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">I started to introduce myself as a project manager to SPATS team.&nbsp; I started to collect action items needed for the SPATS projects.</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">I had a separate teleconference with Neffra Mathews (NOC), Cory Black (Alaska) and Donna Wegner (Montana) to introduce myself as a Project Manager and get a status for the SPATS project.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attended a WO-570 staff meeting to discuss status of the projects and get update from Al&rsquo;Tariq on current projects/status.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-12-21 13:56:25',	4,	'2012-12-26 10:26:12'),
(143,	13,	17,	5,	'2012-12-21',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Data Center Closings</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">: &nbsp;Finalized three more sets of data center closing documents; two small sites and one large site, the latter of which required significant reworking of the cost model to reflect the actual, substantial savings (but also significant up front investment).The California State Office consolidated its data center into that of the Bureau of Reclamation in the same building. &nbsp;Required an investment of &gt;$115K, but net after four years is &gt;$400K. &nbsp;Moving out of the 1016 SF data center allowed them to give up an additional 700 SF, saving nearly $100K/Yr in rent. &nbsp;In addition, the space will be immediately re-let to Fish, which has a serious space shortage.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">New Geospatial Information System (GIS)assignments:</span></span><span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Began studying the GIS Publication Module (GPM) and E-GIS documents to familiarize myself with status of the two projects I am newly assigned to. Both will be reviewed at the 2/6/13 ITIB.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Portfolio Management: </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Assigned to track down status of a ghost project; reported in CPIC as funded, ITAMS (IT Asset Management System) does not appear in any other project rundown. After considerable trial and error, found someone who was familiar with it. &nbsp;It is approved by ITIB, gets put into the budget and approved, so CPIC reports it on the OMB 53 filing, but funds have never been released by the budget office, so no work has actually been done. &nbsp;Turns out there are three project in similar status, although all ostensibly will go forward this year.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completed closure documents</span> for the three sites that will close at the end of the month and delivered to DOI. &nbsp;Campbell Tract, AK, the Arizona State Office and the California State office; will hold a review with state IRM advisors and DOI leads next week.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Met with Duane Dippon (WO300)</span></span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">to discuss new GIS project. &nbsp;He wants to test the ESRI (major GIS supplier) ARCGIS Online product to see if It can satisfy many of the users who now use the licensed product for read ony type activities; The online browser is free; he hopes to eliminate 2/3 of the (currently 4500) licenses the Bureau buys. &nbsp;Will support effort to create Mission Needs Statement.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Briefed CA State IRM Advisor</span>/IRMAC Chair on status of BLM\'s Data Center Consolidation Initiative (DCCI). &nbsp;Rick Shellooe is also on the DOI \"hosting\" committee, tasked with identifying 7 or so major data centers to consolidate all DOI Bureaus into regional (Private cloud?) centers, similar to what is happening in Sacramento with BLM/BOR. Convenient time to start a relationship since we wound up working on the CA State Office closing documents together. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">IRMAC Monthly Conference Call:</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Mr. Shellooe also recommended I attend the IT Resources Management Advisory Committee (IRMAC) monthly conference call and sent me the invite; I did so; very interesting, good background info.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Held telephone review meetings</span> with CA, AK and AZ IRMA\'s regarding documents finalizing their data center closures submittal to DOI. &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Attended weekly GPM Conference Call</span> to begin familiarizing myself with palyers and status of the GIS Publication Module (GPM) for displaying Geophysical Information System (GIS) data from the many different GIS operations throughout the Bureau</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-12-21 16:14:23',	4,	'2012-12-26 10:22:52'),
