(147,	13,	17,	5,	'2012-12-28',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Portfolio Management Research:</strong>&nbsp; Continued researching projects for inclusion in portfolio review.&nbsp; Three projects ostensibly owned by WO500 appear in the CPIC Investment Profiles, two of which appear to be funded.&nbsp; In fact, they have never been funded, but have been tracked&nbsp; as if they were.&nbsp;&nbsp;According to Mr. Samuels, two of them are expected to move forward this year, one under the leadership of WO590, one lead by WO600.&nbsp; Made contact with business owner of the latter who gave me the name of the NOC PM; project is not yet listed on the NOC SharePoint site.&nbsp; Will require more follow-up next week.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Also did further research and study on GIS Publishing Module project and E-GIS tools project, playing catch-up on two large, complex ongoing projects.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>Completed closure documents for 3 DCCI sites.</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Data Center Consolidation:</strong>&nbsp; Reviewed 3 sets of closing documents for Arizona and California State offices, Campbell Tract, AK facility&nbsp;with DOI Leads. &nbsp;I found a couple of errors I had made in the cost models and corrected them, submitted finals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">California State Office in particular is precisely the type of gain OMB was looking for when it started the government-wide initiative; after a relatively small investment, CA will be able to amortize the investment and save more than $400,000 in rent and electricity costs through 2016.&nbsp; DOI asked for a short writeup of the process CA followed so I wrote and submitted it to the responsible parties in Sacramento for review, which they will handle after the holidays. Could be good material for the DOI daily website update</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2012-12-31 09:58:01',	4,	'2013-01-04 23:01:48'),
(148,	16,	18,	6,	'2013-01-04',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">This week, I started to review the Investment Profile (IP) given by Capital Planning and Investment control (CPIC) team.&nbsp; This is part of Project portfolio assignment for WO-200 projects.&nbsp; I needed to work with Project Manager for each WO-200 project and fill in requested information for Office of Management and Budget (OMB).&nbsp; I will be looking at each assigned project from WO-200 and work with the project manager for next 3-4 weeks.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">I contacted Roy King (NOC &ndash; project manager) to discuss all projects assigned to him.&nbsp; I will be setting a conference call next week to explain what information we are looking for in the Investment profile (IP).</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">For the Science Permit Application Tracking System (SPATS), I continued gathering more information about the project status.&nbsp; I tried to contact Kathie Jewel to provide more information about the project but she is on annual leave.&nbsp; I will be starting weekly project status calls in next 2 weeks.</span></p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Started to review Investment Profile (IP) for Recreation Management and Information System (RMIS) and started to understand what information I need to collect from the Project Manager at NOC.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">I had a conference call with Neffra Matthew (from NOC) to discuss next steps for the Science Permit Application Tracking System (SPATS).&nbsp; I have started a doodle poll to find the best day and time for weekly conference call.&nbsp; I would be starting a conference call in next 2 weeks to discuss the project status.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Mohammad and I met for the project status meeting for WO-200.&nbsp; I had given my finding about SPATS and what&rsquo;s next steps needed for the SPATS project.&nbsp; Based on the discussion, I have sent Kathie Jewel (WO-200) an e-mail requesting her help in IT Investment Board (ITIB) for the Science Permit Application Tracking System (SPATS).</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-01-04 15:32:00',	4,	'2013-01-08 17:01:23'),
