(150,	13,	17,	5,	'2013-01-04',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Portfolio Management:</strong>&nbsp; Received distribution of Investment Profile Templates for &ldquo;non-major&rdquo; &nbsp;IT projects and began soliciting assistance for assigned projects.&nbsp; Identified appropriate contacts for first two state projects, Alaska Land Information System, and the General Land Office&rsquo;s Automated Response System and delivered IPs to contacts.&nbsp; Set up initial meeting for next week with GLO personnel and NOC CPIC person (who handles CPIC submissions for all of the systems the NOC manages). &ldquo;Major&rdquo; projects are reported monthly; &ldquo;Non-Major&rdquo; are reported quarterly.&nbsp; Tracked down and made initial contacts for follow-up next week for three more projects Electronic Records Management System (ERMS); IT Asset Management System (ITAMS); and Document Tracking System (DTS).</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Integrated Lifecycle Management Handbook</strong>:&nbsp; Ms. Bowers &amp; I reached agreement that we could expect no more comments on the latest draft from within the division; discussed the methods for actually publishing, who would sign off, etc.&nbsp; Sought counsel from Mr. Landry (acting during Mr. Samuels absence), advised to distribute to States for comment before publication.</p>\r\n</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Data Center Consolidation Initiative:&nbsp; </strong>At Mr. Stingley&rsquo;s request, isolated the extremely small data centers that could be declared to be in their minimum configuration and do a large group closing.&nbsp; This expedited method could mean 19 closings almost immediately, or perhaps in a couple of months&rsquo; effort, leaving only large data centers to focus on for 2013/14.</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>Weekly FDCCI call was uneventful.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-01-08 16:49:18',	4,	'2013-01-11 12:35:32'),
