(152,	13,	17,	5,	'2013-01-11',	'<p><strong>Portfolio Management/Investment Profiles: &nbsp;</strong>Continued researching ghost projects; projects which appear in CPIC to have been functioning for years, that have never, in fact, been funded or developed...and others that apparently have been built that no one knows about.</p>\r\n<p><strong>CARS: Cadastral Automated Response System:</strong>&nbsp; This is apparently a functioning system that was built in connection with the Indian Lawsuit ten years ago. &nbsp;No one at the NOC seems to know of it.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ITAMS: IT Asset Management System:</strong>&nbsp; Appears in CPIC as a funded program years long, it has never been built. &nbsp;Now a strategic initiative in WO 590.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ERMS: &nbsp;Electronic Records Management System:</strong>&nbsp; Another CPIC appearing project that has never been funded, now subject to a DOI moratorium on such systems.</p>',	'<p><strong>Integrated Lifecycle Management: &nbsp;</strong>Input final 590 edits, distributed to several state IT directors, IRMAC chair; final comments prior to publication, aiming for 1/25 final delivery for signature by Mr. Samuels.</p>\r\n<p><strong>GPI/GPM: &nbsp;Geospatial Publication Module:</strong>&nbsp; Spent several hours researching templates for various project artifacts and found we are missing a few. &nbsp;Delivered 9 templates to Business Project Mgr, meeting next week to review..</p>',	'<p><strong>General Land Office Investment Profile: &nbsp;</strong>Hosted teleconference kickoff meeting with GLO and NOC personnel to begin working on filling out the GLO IP. &nbsp;Group agreed to meet again next week to actually populate the document.</p>\r\n<p><strong>EGIS Online: &nbsp;</strong>Met with Duane Dippon to review Mission Needs Statement plans in advance of next ITIB. He plans a test to see if EGIS Online, ESRI\'s Free front end for ARC-GIS can supplant some significant proportion of our fully licensed users, expanding usage while reducing cost. &nbsp;No cost experiment, some question as to whether MNS is appropriate vice basic Project team charter.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ERMS: </strong>&nbsp;Met with Barbara Fergus to discuss earlier mentioned ERMS system; she advised me of the DOI moratorium on e-FOIA and other document storage systems. &nbsp;(DOI is building an enterprise-wide version).Tracked down original moratorium documents, may have an impact on the new project currently contemplated in WO-600, DTS, Document Tracking System. &nbsp;Will explore with business next week.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>None at this time.</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-01-11 16:59:42',	4,	'2013-01-15 14:20:19'),
(153,	16,	18,	6,	'2013-01-11',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">General Project Portfolio activities:</span></strong></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">I started to review Investment Profile (IP) given by Capital Planning and Investment control (CPIC) team.&nbsp; This is part of Project portfolio assignment for WO-200 projects.&nbsp; I am also creating a table with similarities and differences between my projects per request by Mohammad.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span>ESRS, FORVIS, RIPS, Riparian, and RMIS:</span></strong></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">I had a conference call with Roy King (NOC Project Manager) to discuss Investment Profile (IP) for ESRS, FORVIS, RIPS, Riparian and RMIS.</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">I walked through IP for one of the project and explain what needs to be filled in.</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">Roy will talk to Mary Frye who is in charge for updating IP and will f