(155,	13,	17,	5,	'2013-01-18',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Portfolio Management:&nbsp; Application and Data Assessment Tool Inventory: </strong>Began a comparison of known systems in the Portfolio against ADAT Inventory accomplished for DCCI.&nbsp; Found missing surveys, missing Investment Profiles, and numerous previously unknown systems.&nbsp; More work to be done in completely rounding out the IT Investment Portfolios.&nbsp; <strong>Investment Profiles:</strong>&nbsp; Obtained clarification that systems which may never have been reported to OMB may still need to have IP&rsquo;s developed; this was the particular case with BASS, the Bureau Application Security System (the signon system for all internal national apps).&nbsp; Notified PM of need to do the IP.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Data Center Consolidation Initiative</strong>: Exchanged numerous emails with NOC PM regarding the move/closure of the DC Data Center and how to approach.&nbsp; Engineering wants to do a mini project in advance of closure to be sure that what moves to the NOC is sufficient to WO needs; currently there is a serious storage shortage, and no archiving system.&nbsp; Have been pushing NOC to do similar studies on all of the larger data centers so that when the cloud contract is ready, we will know what our needs are, and whether they can be filled.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Cadastral Automated Request System (CARS):</strong>&nbsp; Finally tracked down the right personnel for this application.&nbsp; It is a national system used by Indian Lands Surveyors that is hosted in Portland, OR rather than at the NOC.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Document Tracking System:&nbsp; </strong>Discovered this national system went into production on 12/31/12&hellip;but it has never been presented/approved by ITIB.&nbsp; It is unknown at this time (but unlikely) if they applied for a waiver to build the system despite the long-standing DOI moratorium on document management, tracking and eFOIA systems.&nbsp; Prepared notice for PM noting that it is a national system and recommending they apply for a waiver to DOI moratorium.&nbsp; Briefed management before sending.</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Geospatial Publication Module: 1) </strong>Met with business PM, Beth Wenstrom to review her tasking for outside contractor.&nbsp; Clarified for her the need to do things in sequence, that many of the tasks could not be done until other aspects had been completed first; got her prepared for the meeting with the contractor Friday AM.&nbsp; Her plan when I became involved was to do an RFI.&nbsp; <strong>2)</strong>The Friday meeting, with NOC PM in attendance moved her toward doing a full RFP, to have them do an actual system design and bid it.&nbsp; Contractor would write the RFP per direction. <strong>3)</strong>Also attended the IPT kickoff bringing the team up to speed with activities in the recent month (delivery by contractor of project management documents, planned next steps).</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Investment Profile Development:</strong>&nbsp; <strong>General Land Office:&nbsp; </strong>Attended the review with GLO personnel and NOC CPIC lead in filling out the form.&nbsp; Execllent educational session for me on how to approach the document for a project that has history.&nbsp; Unfortunately, several of mine do not and so will be more difficult.&nbsp; <strong>WO200 Projects:&nbsp; </strong>Joined Chintan Mody&rsquo;s meeting with the NOC CPIC lead and PM who has several of both of our projects.&nbsp; Learned that they have been filling out IP documents all along, apparently the CPIC website template is broken and doesn&rsquo;t update automatically.</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	'<p>Brought the DTS issue to the attention of Mr. Landry; potentially controversial notice (it is correct, but may not be appreciated). &nbsp;He will consider over the long weekend, may review with Mr. Samuels.</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-01-18 16:48:46',	4,	'2013-01-24 21:44:10'),
(156,	16,	18,	6,	'2013-01-18',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">General Project Portfolio activities:</span></strong></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">I am continuing&nbsp;to create the&nbsp;database for the project I have been assigned .&nbsp; I am creating this database so I know what information is missing and what information NOC Project Managers need to fill in before giving this information to the CPIC team.&nbsp; I am working with all project managers to finish this task in the next few weeks.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span>ESRS, FORVIS, RIPS, Riparian, and RMIS:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">I had a conference call with Roy King (NOC Project Manager) to discuss Investment Profile (IP) for ESRS, FORVIS, RIPS, Riparian and RMIS.&nbsp; Roy is working with Mary Frye (NOC) to get necessary information to finish IPs.&nbsp; Roy will provide updates as more information is available for WO-570 to review the IPs before sending them to CPIC team.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;