IS and WHBPS.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	'<p>na</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-01-22 11:39:22',	4,	'2013-01-24 21:52:42'),
(157,	16,	18,	6,	'2013-01-25',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">General Project Portfolio activities:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">I met with Mohammad for the weekly meeting to discuss status of projects that I have been assigned.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">RAS:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">I had a conference call with Joe Manke (NOC Project manager), Mary Frye (NOC CPIC POC), Kimberly Hackett (WO Program Rep) and Kathie Jewell (WO 200 IRM advisor) to discuss Investment profile (IP).</span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">In the meeting, everyone took action to fill in the appropriate section and will return&nbsp;in a few weeks to finish this project.</span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Once completed by team, IP will be reviewed by WO-500 before submitting to DOI CPIC team.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">PRIS:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">In order to complete Investment profile (IP) for Protection and Response Information System (PRIS), I had a conference call with Joe Manke (NOC Project manager), Mary Frye (NOC CPIC POC), Georgette Fogle (WO Program Rep), Suzanne Buntrock (NOC User Rep).</span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">In the meeting, everyone took action to fill in the appropriate sections and&nbsp;will return&nbsp;in a few weeks to finish this project.</span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Once completed by team, IP will be reviewed by WO-500 before submitting to DOI CPIC team.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">RAS and PRIS:</span></strong></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">For the Protection and Response Information System (PRIS) and the Rangeland Administration System (RAS) IT application, I met with Technical Project manager, Program Manager, Business Manager, User group rep started to work on Investment profile (IP). </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">For RAS and PRIS meeting, I have sent meeting minutes and action items from these meeting to Joe Manke (Project Manager) for his review.&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">General Project Portfolio activities:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Mohammad and I met for the project status meeting for WO-200.&nbsp; I have given updates about RAS and PRIS during this meeting.&nbsp; I have also given status of SPATS project.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">RAS:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>I had a conference call with Joe Manke (NOC Project Manager), Kimberly </span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">Hackett (WO Program Rep), Mary Frye (NOC CPIC POC), and Kathie Jewell (WO 200 IRM advisor) to discuss the Investment Profile (IP).</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong style=\"line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">PRIS:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">I had a conference call with Joe Manke (NOC Project manager), Mary Frye (NOC CPIC POC), Georgette Fogle (WO Program Rep), Suzanne Buntrock (NOC User Rep) to discuss the Investment Profile (IP).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-01-25 15:12:56',	4,	'2013-01-29 12:28:11'),
(158,	13,	17,	5,	'2013-01-25',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Geospatial Publishing Module (GPM): &nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Made careful edits to the Project Management Plan and Requirements Management Plan, to limit (constrain) the scope of the initial module. &nbsp;Tendency is to add in more and more features, increasing time to delivery and cost. &nbsp;Constrained the Initial GPM to replace ONLY GeoCommunicator (GC). &nbsp;There are at least 5-6 additional systems identified that the business wishes to add into the ultimate version of the GPM in the future. &nbsp;As it is, the new GPM will have to publish across 14 different systems and types of data to replace GC.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Portfolio Management:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; Reminded PM\'s of my sub-portfolio that Investment Profiles are due for non-major projects on 1/31. &nbsp;So far, responses have not been comforting, ranging from \"We\'re not doing that\" and \"I\'m too busy to do that\" to \"Gee, it\'s too bad all of your projects have problems that make that deadline difficult.\" &nbsp;Meeting with CPIC next week to discuss possible strategies.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">Portfolio Management Summary:</span></strong><span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">&nbsp;Provided inputs and edits to the summary report being prepared by Ms. Bowers.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">Portfolio Management:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">&nbsp; Ongoing research in support of Investment Profiles has identified a number of active projects identified in CPIC that do not have 2013 templates. &nbsp;In review of Applications and Data Assessment Tool (ADAT) reports compiled for Data Center Consolidation Initiative (DCCI), discovered that there are numerous active systems that are not identified as CPIC Assets. &nbsp;Meeting with CPIC personnel next week to discuss these and other issues.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">DCCI/ Nevada State Office (NVSO): &nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Phone meeting with state IT director and NOC personnel to discuss their desire to perform consolidation activities by the end of this year, significantly earlier than planned. &nbsp;Extremely useful to have highly motivated people out in front of the situation! &nbsp;They have a sensible, well thought out plan that appears imminently doable.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">GPM: &nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Attended phone meeting with Business Area\'s contractor who is supporting them with documentation assistance, to discuss next steps, first being development of a Request for Proposals. &nbsp;Broad discussion of level of deteail to be included in the RFP, whether more detailed requirements are needed. &nbsp;Due to time constraints, the direction the business seems to be heading is to have the contractor do its own design, leaving it wide open as to arechitecture. &nbsp;Constraints again become a factor.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>See below</p>',	'<p><strong>Governance: &nbsp;</strong>Concerns about our ability to enforce policy, information requests for Investment Profiles, ITIB reporting, overall governance. &nbsp;Had discussions with Mr.Landry (acting Div.Ch.) and Ms. Bowers; Mr. Landry had discussions with Mr. Samuels and Ms Jollay, same subject. &nbsp;Assume there will be further discussion/direction next week.</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-01-25 16:16:24',	4,	'2013-01-31 21:54:26'),
