(163,	16,	18,	6,	'2013-02-08',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">SPATS:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">As part of action item for the Science Permit application tracking (SPATS) project, I started to work on the Business Case and Charter this week.&nbsp; I have created a draft version of business case and charter which was reviewed by Mohammad. &nbsp;I still need to fill out few sections which would require team meeting or Subject Matter expert\'s input.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">I have contacted the subject matter expert (SME) for Enterprise architecture (EA) and Security and Privacy officer to fill in the appropriate section for SPATS business Case.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">SPATS:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">I have created SPATS business case and Charter draft version which was reviewed by Mohammad in our weekly project status meeting.&nbsp; Mohammad has suggested some changes based on initial draft review.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">General:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Attend a WO-570 staff meeting to discuss status of the projects and get update from Al&rsquo;Tariq on current projects/status.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;\">I met with Mohammad to give status of my project for our weekly meeting.&nbsp; In this meeting, I showed him the draft version of SPATS business case and Charter.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>SPATS</strong>:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;\">I had a conference call with Matt Cahill (NOC &ndash; IT Security Point of contact) to discuss Security and Privacy section in the business case for SPATS.&nbsp; I followed up with detail information about SPATS and what exactly I was looking to get from the subject matter expert (SME).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt;\">I met with Christine Hawkinson (Acting EA lead) to discuss SPATS project.&nbsp; She would look in to EA section for SPATS.</span></p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	'<p>n/a</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-02-08 15:29:57',	4,	'2013-02-15 11:58:18'),
(164,	13,	17,	5,	'2013-02-08',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;<strong>Portfolio Management: &nbsp;</strong><strong>Alaska Land Information System (ALIS): </strong>Conducted research to determine veracity of a claim made to 590 that the &ldquo;New&rdquo; ALIS (which has been under construction for some time) was &ldquo;approved&rdquo; by ITIB last year. &nbsp;Proposals have been made and approved on multiple occasions to go forward to build a Business Case and create Mission needs Statement to actually merge ALIS and Legacy Rehost 2000.&nbsp; No indication that either of those tasks has been performed, no indication that authority was given to spend money or perform development.&nbsp; ALIS and LR2000 perform very similar functions, for Alaska and CONUS; ALIS is more feature-packed so is a good replacement candidate&hellip;but is hosted on very old technology that needs updating.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Integrated Lifecycle Management (ILM): &nbsp;</strong>At MS Bowers\' request, transmitted the ILM handbook and Templates to the PPM Tool Contractor for background on what we will be doing with the tool. Also at her request, began creating a \"work breakdown structure\", a graphical listing of the various artifacts that must be delivered at various times throughout the Lifecycle to obtain ITIB approvals.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\"><strong>Portfolio Management: State-Level Applications: </strong>Developed a list of state-level applications for potential future inclusion in the portfolio management schema&nbsp;by reviewing the recently-completed ADAT surveys.&nbsp; List includes more than sixty systems unique to BLM.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\"><strong>General Land Office (GLO):&nbsp; </strong>In a meeting the previous week, I reported&nbsp;on upgrades the NOC is performing for GLO; Server replacement, additional storage and a new archiving system Received direction from Mr. Samuels to determine funding source for the upgrades.&nbsp; Ultimately confirmed with GLO personnel that it was budgeted and included in their 2013 spend plan.</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Geospatial Publication Module:&nbsp; </strong>Meeting to review ITIB finding; moving forward with RFP in preparation for the Monday meeting with the subcontractor who will write the RFP.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>FDCCI :&nbsp; </strong>Weekly call introduced a new rating system for determining &ldquo;core&rdquo; data centers.&nbsp; Nine factor rating system draws data from the Total Cost of Ownership model.&nbsp; Initial task is to review the descriptive papers, distributed to DOI and one other agency.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Joined meeting with NOC project management (A. Torres, K. Wilbert) to review rating document, added DOI lead to the call to address a couple questions.&nbsp; Mr. Wilbert will summarize comments and report to DOI by due date next Monday.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>',	'<p>None</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-02-08 16:12:05',	4,	'2013-02-15 12:01:55'),
