erif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><strong>General Land Office Automated Records System (GLO):</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><strong style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"line-height: 12.6pt; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">1)<strong>&nbsp;</strong>NOC engineering performed a server upgrade last week that resulted in a marked improvement in performance. &nbsp;Also added significant additional storage capacity and this week they are installing a backup/archiving system, securing the GLO data for the first time.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2) The GLO quarterly Investment Profile was submitted on time on 1/31/13.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><strong>Geospatial Publication Module (GPM):&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">1)&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">ITIB last week gave authorization to move forward with an RFP and agreed to allocate&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">$900K toward the project.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2) Reviewed activities in the Monday biweekly meeting and provided business case template&nbsp;to IRM Advisor.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3) Reviewed the<strong>&nbsp;</strong>consultant&rsquo;s proposal for creating the RFP.&nbsp; Offered&nbsp;suggestions for&nbsp;inclusion in the SOW.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><strong>Steady State</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #595959; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt;\">The following applications/systems are in steady-state operation &amp; maintenance.</span><span style=\"color: #595959; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #595959; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Portfolio management oversight activities are being performed including the verification that systems are operating as expected and meet standards for availability, reliability and security.</span><span style=\"color: #595959; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #595959; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt;\">The system&rsquo;s Owners and Stakeholders are periodically queried to identify new requirements, technical advances, and overall system needs.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"color: #595959; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">Bureau Application Security System (BASS)</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Cadastral Automated Request System (CARS)&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Enterprise Geospatial Information System (eGIS)</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">GeoCommunicator (GC)&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt;\">Geographic Coordinate Data Base Data Preparation System (GCDB)</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Information Technology Asset Management System (ITAMS)</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: normal;\">Integrated Lifecycle Management (ILM) Handbook:</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;1) Completed a Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) graphic outlining deliverable artifacts by&nbsp;ILM Phase.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><strong style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Portfolio Management:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background: #FAFAFA;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">1) Completed</span><strong style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">a more comprehensive listing of BLM systems to be to be tracked in the IT</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">Portfolios and delivered to the Portfolio Managers. Identified some 30 systems that are not</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 12.6pt;\">currently tracked.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;<strong style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Geospatial Publication Module: &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: 12.6pt; background: #FAFAFA;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1)&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Created a graphical WBS representation of the deliverable artifacts by ILM&nbsp;&nbsp;phase and&nbsp;transmitted to the consultant that will be producing the RFP for the Geospatial Publication&nbsp;Module.</span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"line-height: 12.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">GPM: &nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Biweekly conference call reviewed the proposal from the consultant who will draft the RFP and determined next steps forward after receiving authority for the RFP from ITIB last week.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><strong>DCCI:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;Weekly call cancelled due to travel schedules.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">ILM:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Meeting the last week in February with NOC representatives to review their consolidated comments, final meeting before publication.</span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: normal;\">Requests for Investment Profiles resulted in considerable pushback from PMs on certain systems. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; 1) BASS PM basically refused, claiming the app is just a tool;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2) Oregon claims theirs is not a national app.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;3) In addition to rebaseline problem for eGIS, PM objected to doing 2014 numbers for GeoCommunicator, system that will be replaced by GPM; and GPM is not far enough along&nbsp;to do an IP.</span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>N/A</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-02-15 15:25:02',	4,	'2013-03-07 09:54:59'),
