nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ITAMS (Study being performed by WO590-not an active system)</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>GPM:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Per request of business manager (BM), uploaded project planning templates to the project website.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Portfolio Management:&nbsp;</strong>Compiled documentation evidencing the 30-40 BLM created operational systems that are not tracked in CPIC, using documentation from several BLM SharePoint sites and DOI ADAT surveys.&nbsp; Presented to PfM team in meeting.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2/25</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Portfolio Management Team:</strong>&nbsp; Met to seek guidance, establish policy for systems outside the &nbsp;currently tracked portfolios. Consensus view that eventually we will track everything, but until we have gotten a firm grip on current major and non-major projects we will not attempt to track anything further&hellip;but continue to record new untracked systems for later.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>GPM Biweekly</strong>:&nbsp; Cancelled by Business owner</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2/27</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Portfolio Manager</strong>: To discuss restart of documentation efforts for new PPM tool, and newly released NOC &ldquo;Operational Readiness Documentation&rdquo; package with emphasis on security.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>FDCCI:</strong> Cancelled by DOI Lead.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2/28</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>ILM:</strong> Face to Face meeting with NOC reps was cancelled due to sequester, met via phone to discuss their comments. Raised some fundamental issues that will need work. Claimed there are some 200 comments, but have not received them yet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">2/29</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>BLM Privacy Officer</strong>: Sought guidance on PIA template for PPM tool project.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: #fafafa;\"><strong>ALIS:</strong><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>It appears that the interim version of ALIS, ALIS II has never been presented or at least, has never been approved for development by ITIB.&nbsp;(they were directed to do a business case, but none was ever presented to ITIB). &nbsp;A grant from WO300 was discussed not necessarily in the context of new development but rather in keeping the system running.New ALIS II is nearly ready. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Seeking guidance on how to proceed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	2,	4,	'2013-03-01 16:35:17',	4,	'2013-03-07 10:56:32'),
(180,	13,	17,	5,	'2013-03-08',	'<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Portfolio Management:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">ALIS:&nbsp; </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Seeking procedural guidance regarding near-complete ALIS II development never approved by ITIB.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">eGIS:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp; Testing of ESRI Online has resumed after security problem was resolved (anything originating from the Amazon cloud was being rejected). Rollout of ArcGIS 10.1 is half complete nationwide.&nbsp; Asked PM to update NOC SharePoint dashboard to reflect current status.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">GPM:&nbsp; </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Produced an explanation of 3 documents I uploaded to GPM SharePoint site (actually for LR2000 team). Business area unfamiliar with PIA, Scope Statement and Project Process Agreement. Reviewed documents in anticipation of Wednesday meeting; unfortunately, while the government was closed in DC, the meeting was held anyway.&nbsp; Biweekly Tech Team meetings resume next week</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">PPM Tool:&nbsp; </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Resolved the final open issue (records retention) to complete the Privacy Impact Assessment (PIA) Document. No word yet on who the PM is to be. Continued work on Risk Management Plan.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">Steady-State: &nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"color: #595959; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">The following applications/systems are steady-state.&nbsp; Portfolio management oversight activities are being performed, including verification that systems are operating as expected and meeting the required standards for availability, reliability and security. System owners and stakeholders are periodically queried to identify new requirements, technical advances and overall system needs.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt; color: #595959;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-size: 10.5pt; color: #7f7f7f;\"><span style=\"color: windowtext;\">ALIS &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BASS</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CARS</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DTS</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; eGIS</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; GCDB</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; GeoCommunicator</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; GLO</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; color: #595959; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-themetint: 166;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ITAMS (Study to be &nbsp;performed by WO590-not an active system)</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Integrated Lifecycle Management:&nbsp; </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Conducted preliminary review of NOC comments. Appears that about 1/3 of comments are regarding Privacy/Security, so forwarded the doc to IA; also supplied it to new Portfolio Manager for Infrastructure. Many highly substantive comments will require significant efforts to resolve issues.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Data Center Consolidation Initiative:&nbsp; </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Received a tasking request from DOI Lead through BLM PM to produce comments on OMB&rsquo;s TCO Cost Model. Commenced work on comments, should finish next week.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">PPM Tool</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1.&nbsp; Delivered PIA Document for PPM Tool to Portfolio Manager.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2.&nbsp; Delivered preliminary Project Process Agreement &nbsp;for PPM &nbsp;Tool to PfM.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Portfolio Management</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1.&nbsp;Delivered to PM preliminary reduced-footprint Investment &nbsp;Profile for<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>tracking small projects/systems not reported to OMB<span style=\"white-space: pre;\">.</span>.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">3/4/13</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Melillo--consultant for PPM tool install to go over initial desires of WO 570 staff, prior to formal interviews.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">3/5/13</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">Missed two meetings due to snow closure, GPM/DCCI. &nbsp;Received an assignment in DCCI meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'<p><strong>PPM Tool</strong>: &nbsp;No PM active/assigned...risk.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ALIS: &nbsp;</strong>Way forward is unclear...potential political issues.</p>',	'<p>None.</p>',	1,	13,	'2013-03-08 11:36:17',	4,	'2013-03-11 01:05:41'),
(181,	16,	18,	6,	'2013-03-08',	'<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">FORVIS</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">(1)<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Reviewed the Investment Profile (IP) before submission to DOI and OMB. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">(2)<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Created a database for&nbsp;issues during the review for feedback to the NOC Project Manager and resolve the issues before submission to DOI and OMB</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">RIPARIAN</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">(1)<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Monitoring Riparian going through Final Customer Quality testing. &nbsp;Not seeing any major issue at this point. &nbsp;Expect the customer testing to be finished by end of March.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Project Portfolio Management Tool Implementation</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">(1)<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Attended a meeting with third party consultants to describe the Business Process for WO-570 for managing the Portfolio/Project</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">(2)<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Described the issues/gaps in the current business process based on my